24// Adds Arm-specific methods for generating InstructionOperands.
25template <typename Adapter>
26class ArmOperandGeneratorT : public OperandGeneratorT<Adapter> {
27 public:
28 OPERAND_GENERATOR_T_BOILERPLATE(Adapter)
29
30 explicit ArmOperandGeneratorT(InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>* selector)
31 : super(selector) {}
32
33 bool CanBeImmediate(int32_t value) const {
34 return Assembler::ImmediateFitsAddrMode1Instruction(value);
35 }
36
37 bool CanBeImmediate(uint32_t value) const {
38 return CanBeImmediate(base::bit_cast<int32_t>(value));
39 }
40
41 bool CanBeImmediate(node_t node, InstructionCode opcode) {
42 if (!selector()->is_integer_constant(node)) return false;
43 int64_t value64 = selector()->integer_constant(node);
44 DCHECK(base::IsInRange(value64, std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min(),
45 std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::max()));
46 int32_t value = static_cast<int32_t>(value64);
47 switch (ArchOpcodeField::decode(opcode)) {
48 case kArmAnd:
49 case kArmMov:
50 case kArmMvn:
51 case kArmBic:
52 return CanBeImmediate(value) || CanBeImmediate(~value);
53
54 case kArmAdd:
55 case kArmSub:
56 case kArmCmp:
57 case kArmCmn:
58 return CanBeImmediate(value) || CanBeImmediate(-value);
59
60 case kArmTst:
61 case kArmTeq:
62 case kArmOrr:
63 case kArmEor:
64 case kArmRsb:
65 return CanBeImmediate(value);
66
67 case kArmVldrF32:
68 case kArmVstrF32:
69 case kArmVldrF64:
70 case kArmVstrF64:
71 return value >= -1020 && value <= 1020 && (value % 4) == 0;
72
73 case kArmLdrb:
74 case kArmLdrsb:
75 case kArmStrb:
76 case kArmLdr:
77 case kArmStr:
78 return value >= -4095 && value <= 4095;
79
80 case kArmLdrh:
81 case kArmLdrsh:
82 case kArmStrh:
83 return value >= -255 && value <= 255;
84
85 default:
86 break;
87 }
88 return false;
89 }
90};

111#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
112void VisitSimdShiftRRR(InstructionSelectorT<TurboshaftAdapter>* selector,
113 ArchOpcode opcode, turboshaft::OpIndex node, int width) {
114 using namespace turboshaft; // NOLINT(build/namespaces)
115 ArmOperandGeneratorT<TurboshaftAdapter> g(selector);
116 const Simd128ShiftOp& op = selector->Get(node).Cast<Simd128ShiftOp>();
117 int32_t shift_by;
118 if (selector->MatchIntegralWord32Constant(op.shift(), &shift_by)) {
119 if (shift_by % width == 0) {
120 selector->EmitIdentity(node);
121 } else {
122 selector->Emit(opcode, g.DefineAsRegister(node),
123 g.UseRegister(op.input()), g.UseImmediate(op.shift()));
124 }
125 } else {
126 VisitRRR(selector, opcode, node);
127 }
128}
129
130void VisitSimdShiftRRR(InstructionSelectorT<TurbofanAdapter>* selector,
131 ArchOpcode opcode, Node* node, int width) {
132 ArmOperandGeneratorT<TurbofanAdapter> g(selector);
133 Int32Matcher m(node->InputAt(1));
134 if (m.HasResolvedValue()) {
135 if (m.IsMultipleOf(width)) {
136 selector->EmitIdentity(node);
137 } else {
138 selector->Emit(opcode, g.DefineAsRegister(node),
139 g.UseRegister(node->InputAt(0)),
140 g.UseImmediate(node->InputAt(1)));
141 }
142 } else {
143 VisitRRR(selector, opcode, node);
144 }
145}

147template <typename Adapter>
148void VisitRRRShuffle(InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>* selector, ArchOpcode opcode,
149 typename Adapter::node_t node,
150 typename Adapter::node_t input0,
151 typename Adapter::node_t input1) {
152 ArmOperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(selector);
153 // Swap inputs to save an instruction in the CodeGenerator for High ops.
154 if (opcode == kArmS32x4ZipRight || opcode == kArmS32x4UnzipRight ||
155 opcode == kArmS32x4TransposeRight || opcode == kArmS16x8ZipRight ||
156 opcode == kArmS16x8UnzipRight || opcode == kArmS16x8TransposeRight ||
157 opcode == kArmS8x16ZipRight || opcode == kArmS8x16UnzipRight ||
158 opcode == kArmS8x16TransposeRight) {
159 std::swap(input0, input1);
160 }
161 // Use DefineSameAsFirst for binary ops that clobber their inputs, e.g. the
162 // NEON vzip, vuzp, and vtrn instructions.
163 selector->Emit(opcode, g.DefineSameAsFirst(node), g.UseRegister(input0),
164 g.UseRegister(input1));
165}

167template <typename Adapter>
168void VisitRRI(InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>* selector, ArchOpcode opcode,
169 typename Adapter::node_t node) {
170 ArmOperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(selector);
171 if constexpr (Adapter::IsTurboshaft) {
172 using namespace turboshaft; // NOLINT(build/namespaces)
173 const Operation& op = selector->Get(node);
174 int imm = op.template Cast<Simd128ExtractLaneOp>().lane;
175 selector->Emit(opcode, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(op.input(0)),
176 g.UseImmediate(imm));
177 } else {
178 int32_t imm = OpParameter<int32_t>(node->op());
179 selector->Emit(opcode, g.DefineAsRegister(node),
180 g.UseRegister(node->InputAt(0)), g.UseImmediate(imm));
181 }
182}

184template <typename Adapter>
185void VisitRRIR(InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>* selector, ArchOpcode opcode,
186 typename Adapter::node_t node) {
187 ArmOperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(selector);
188 if constexpr (Adapter::IsTurboshaft) {
189 using namespace turboshaft; // NOLINT(build/namespaces)
190 const turboshaft::Simd128ReplaceLaneOp& op =
191 selector->Get(node).template Cast<turboshaft::Simd128ReplaceLaneOp>();
192 selector->Emit(opcode, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(op.into()),
193 g.UseImmediate(op.lane), g.UseUniqueRegister(op.new_lane()));
194 } else {
195 int32_t imm = OpParameter<int32_t>(node->op());
196 selector->Emit(opcode, g.DefineAsRegister(node),
197 g.UseRegister(node->InputAt(0)), g.UseImmediate(imm),
198 g.UseUniqueRegister(node->InputAt(1)));
199 }
200}

203template <IrOpcode::Value kOpcode, int kImmMin, int kImmMax,
204 AddressingMode kImmMode, AddressingMode kRegMode>
205bool TryMatchShift(InstructionSelectorT<TurbofanAdapter>* selector,
206 InstructionCode* opcode_return, Node* node,
207 InstructionOperand* value_return,
208 InstructionOperand* shift_return) {
209 ArmOperandGeneratorT<TurbofanAdapter> g(selector);
210 if (node->opcode() == kOpcode) {
211 Int32BinopMatcher m(node);
212 *value_return = g.UseRegister(m.left().node());
213 if (m.right().IsInRange(kImmMin, kImmMax)) {
214 *opcode_return |= AddressingModeField::encode(kImmMode);
215 *shift_return = g.UseImmediate(m.right().node());
216 } else {
217 *opcode_return |= AddressingModeField::encode(kRegMode);
218 *shift_return = g.UseRegister(m.right().node());
219 }
220 return true;
221 }
222 return false;
223}
224
225template <typename OpmaskT, int kImmMin, int kImmMax, AddressingMode kImmMode,
226 AddressingMode kRegMode>
227bool TryMatchShift(InstructionSelectorT<TurboshaftAdapter>* selector,
228 InstructionCode* opcode_return, turboshaft::OpIndex node,
229 InstructionOperand* value_return,
230 InstructionOperand* shift_return) {
231 using namespace turboshaft; // NOLINT(build/namespaces)
232 ArmOperandGeneratorT<TurboshaftAdapter> g(selector);
233 const Operation& op = selector->Get(node);
234 if (op.Is<OpmaskT>()) {
235 const ShiftOp& shift = op.Cast<ShiftOp>();
236 *value_return = g.UseRegister(shift.left());
237 int32_t shift_by;
238 if (selector->MatchIntegralWord32Constant(shift.right(), &shift_by) &&
239 base::IsInRange(shift_by, kImmMin, kImmMax)) {
240 *opcode_return |= AddressingModeField::encode(kImmMode);
241 *shift_return = g.UseImmediate(shift.right());
242 } else {
243 *opcode_return |= AddressingModeField::encode(kRegMode);
244 *shift_return = g.UseRegister(shift.right());
245 }
246 return true;
247 }
248 return false;
249}
250
251template <IrOpcode::Value kOpcode, int kImmMin, int kImmMax,
252 AddressingMode kImmMode>
253bool TryMatchShiftImmediate(InstructionSelectorT<TurbofanAdapter>* selector,
254 InstructionCode* opcode_return, Node* node,
255 InstructionOperand* value_return,
256 InstructionOperand* shift_return) {
257 ArmOperandGeneratorT<TurbofanAdapter> g(selector);
258 if (node->opcode() == kOpcode) {
259 Int32BinopMatcher m(node);
260 if (m.right().IsInRange(kImmMin, kImmMax)) {
261 *opcode_return |= AddressingModeField::encode(kImmMode);
262 *value_return = g.UseRegister(m.left().node());
263 *shift_return = g.UseImmediate(m.right().node());
264 return true;
265 }
266 }
267 return false;
268}

270template <typename OpmaskT, int kImmMin, int kImmMax, AddressingMode kImmMode>
271bool TryMatchShiftImmediate(InstructionSelectorT<TurboshaftAdapter>* selector,
272 InstructionCode* opcode_return,
273 turboshaft::OpIndex node,
274 InstructionOperand* value_return,
275 InstructionOperand* shift_return) {
276 using namespace turboshaft; // NOLINT(build/namespaces)
277 ArmOperandGeneratorT<TurboshaftAdapter> g(selector);
278 const Operation& op = selector->Get(node);
279 if (op.Is<OpmaskT>()) {
280 const ShiftOp& shift = op.Cast<ShiftOp>();
281 int32_t shift_by;
282 if (selector->MatchIntegralWord32Constant(shift.right(), &shift_by) &&
283 base::IsInRange(shift_by, kImmMin, kImmMax)) {
284 *opcode_return |= AddressingModeField::encode(kImmMode);
285 *value_return = g.UseRegister(shift.left());
286 *shift_return = g.UseImmediate(shift.right());
287 return true;
288 }
289 }
290 return false;
291}

399template <typename Adapter>
400bool TryMatchShift(InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>* selector,
401 InstructionCode* opcode_return,
402 typename Adapter::node_t node,
403 InstructionOperand* value_return,
404 InstructionOperand* shift_return) {
405 return (
406 TryMatchASR(selector, opcode_return, node, value_return, shift_return) ||
407 TryMatchLSL(selector, opcode_return, node, value_return, shift_return) ||
408 TryMatchLSR(selector, opcode_return, node, value_return, shift_return) ||
409 TryMatchROR(selector, opcode_return, node, value_return, shift_return));
410}

412template <typename Adapter>
413bool TryMatchImmediateOrShift(InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>* selector,
414 InstructionCode* opcode_return,
415 typename Adapter::node_t node,
416 size_t* input_count_return,
417 InstructionOperand* inputs) {
418 ArmOperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(selector);
419 if (g.CanBeImmediate(node, *opcode_return)) {
420 *opcode_return |= AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_Operand2_I);
421 inputs[0] = g.UseImmediate(node);
422 *input_count_return = 1;
423 return true;
424 }
425 if (TryMatchShift(selector, opcode_return, node, &inputs[0], &inputs[1])) {
426 *input_count_return = 2;
427 return true;
428 }
429 return false;
430}

432template <typename Adapter>
433void VisitBinop(InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>* selector,
434 typename Adapter::node_t node, InstructionCode opcode,
435 InstructionCode reverse_opcode,
436 FlagsContinuationT<Adapter>* cont) {
437 using node_t = typename Adapter::node_t;
438 ArmOperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(selector);
439 node_t lhs = selector->input_at(node, 0);
440 node_t rhs = selector->input_at(node, 1);
441 InstructionOperand inputs[3];
442 size_t input_count = 0;
443 InstructionOperand outputs[1];
444 size_t output_count = 0;
445
446 if (lhs == rhs) {
447 // If both inputs refer to the same operand, enforce allocating a register
448 // for both of them to ensure that we don't end up generating code like
449 // this:
450 //
451 // mov r0, r1, asr #16
452 // adds r0, r0, r1, asr #16
453 // bvs label
454 InstructionOperand const input = g.UseRegister(lhs);
455 opcode |= AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_Operand2_R);
456 inputs[input_count++] = input;
457 inputs[input_count++] = input;
458 } else if (TryMatchImmediateOrShift(selector, &opcode, rhs, &input_count,
459 &inputs[1])) {
460 inputs[0] = g.UseRegister(lhs);
461 input_count++;
462 } else if (TryMatchImmediateOrShift(selector, &reverse_opcode, lhs,
463 &input_count, &inputs[1])) {
464 inputs[0] = g.UseRegister(rhs);
465 opcode = reverse_opcode;
466 input_count++;
467 } else {
468 opcode |= AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_Operand2_R);
469 inputs[input_count++] = g.UseRegister(lhs);
470 inputs[input_count++] = g.UseRegister(rhs);
471 }
472
473 outputs[output_count++] = g.DefineAsRegister(node);
474
475 DCHECK_NE(0u, input_count);
476 DCHECK_EQ(1u, output_count);
477 DCHECK_GE(arraysize(inputs), input_count);
478 DCHECK_GE(arraysize(outputs), output_count);
479 DCHECK_NE(kMode_None, AddressingModeField::decode(opcode));
480
481 selector->EmitWithContinuation(opcode, output_count, outputs, input_count,
482 inputs, cont);
483}

485template <typename Adapter>
486void VisitBinop(InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>* selector,
487 typename Adapter::node_t node, InstructionCode opcode,
488 InstructionCode reverse_opcode) {
489 FlagsContinuationT<Adapter> cont;

493template <typename Adapter>
494void EmitDiv(InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>* selector, ArchOpcode div_opcode,
495 ArchOpcode f64i32_opcode, ArchOpcode i32f64_opcode,
496 InstructionOperand result_operand, InstructionOperand left_operand,
497 InstructionOperand right_operand) {
498 ArmOperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(selector);
499 if (selector->IsSupported(SUDIV)) {
500 selector->Emit(div_opcode, result_operand, left_operand, right_operand);
501 return;
502 }
503 InstructionOperand left_double_operand = g.TempDoubleRegister();
504 InstructionOperand right_double_operand = g.TempDoubleRegister();
505 InstructionOperand result_double_operand = g.TempDoubleRegister();
506 selector->Emit(f64i32_opcode, left_double_operand, left_operand);
507 selector->Emit(f64i32_opcode, right_double_operand, right_operand);
508 selector->Emit(kArmVdivF64, result_double_operand, left_double_operand,
509 right_double_operand);
510 selector->Emit(i32f64_opcode, result_operand, result_double_operand);
511}

519 g.DefineAsRegister(node),
520 g.UseRegister(selector->input_at(node, 0)),
521 g.UseRegister(selector->input_at(node, 1)));

524template <typename Adapter>
525void VisitMod(InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>* selector,
526 typename Adapter::node_t node, ArchOpcode div_opcode,
527 ArchOpcode f64i32_opcode, ArchOpcode i32f64_opcode) {
528 ArmOperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(selector);
529 InstructionOperand div_operand = g.TempRegister();
530 InstructionOperand result_operand = g.DefineAsRegister(node);
531 InstructionOperand left_operand = g.UseRegister(selector->input_at(node, 0));
532 InstructionOperand right_operand = g.UseRegister(selector->input_at(node, 1));
533 EmitDiv(selector, div_opcode, f64i32_opcode, i32f64_opcode, div_operand,
534 left_operand, right_operand);
535 if (selector->IsSupported(ARMv7)) {
536 selector->Emit(kArmMls, result_operand, div_operand, right_operand,
537 left_operand);
538 } else {
539 InstructionOperand mul_operand = g.TempRegister();
540 selector->Emit(kArmMul, mul_operand, div_operand, right_operand);
541 selector->Emit(kArmSub | AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_Operand2_R),
542 result_operand, left_operand, mul_operand);
543 }
544}

546// Adds the base and offset into a register, then change the addressing
547// mode of opcode_return to use this register. Certain instructions, e.g.
548// vld1 and vst1, when given two registers, will post-increment the offset, i.e.
549// perform the operation at base, then add offset to base. What we intend is to
550// access at (base+offset).
551template <typename Adapter>
552void EmitAddBeforeS128LoadStore(InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>* selector,
553 InstructionCode* opcode_return,
554 size_t* input_count_return,
555 InstructionOperand* inputs) {
556 ArmOperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(selector);
557 InstructionOperand addr = g.TempRegister();
558 InstructionCode op = kArmAdd;
559 op |= AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_Operand2_R);
560 selector->Emit(op, 1, &addr, 2, inputs);
561 *opcode_return |= AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_Operand2_R);
562 *input_count_return -= 1;
563 inputs[0] = addr;
564}

566void EmitLoad(InstructionSelectorT<TurboshaftAdapter>* selector,
567 InstructionCode opcode, InstructionOperand* output,
568 turboshaft::OpIndex base, turboshaft::OpIndex index) {
569 using namespace turboshaft; // NOLINT(build/namespaces)
570 ArmOperandGeneratorT<TurboshaftAdapter> g(selector);
571 InstructionOperand inputs[3];
572 size_t input_count = 2;
573
574 const Operation& base_op = selector->Get(base);
575 if (base_op.Is<Opmask::kExternalConstant>() &&
576 selector->is_integer_constant(index)) {
577 const ConstantOp& constant_base = base_op.Cast<ConstantOp>();
578 if (selector->CanAddressRelativeToRootsRegister(
579 constant_base.external_reference())) {
580 ptrdiff_t const delta =
581 selector->integer_constant(index) +
582 MacroAssemblerBase::RootRegisterOffsetForExternalReference(
583 selector->isolate(), constant_base.external_reference());
584 input_count = 1;
585 inputs[0] = g.UseImmediate(static_cast<int32_t>(delta));
586 opcode |= AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_Root);
587 selector->Emit(opcode, 1, output, input_count, inputs);
588 return;
589 }
590 }
591
592 if (base_op.Is<LoadRootRegisterOp>()) {
593 input_count = 1;
594 // This will only work if {index} is a constant.
595 inputs[0] = g.UseImmediate(index);
596 opcode |= AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_Root);
597 selector->Emit(opcode, 1, output, input_count, inputs);
598 return;
599 }
600
601 inputs[0] = g.UseRegister(base);
602 if (g.CanBeImmediate(index, opcode)) {
603 inputs[1] = g.UseImmediate(index);
604 opcode |= AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_Offset_RI);
605 } else if ((opcode == kArmLdr) &&
606 TryMatchLSLImmediate(selector, &opcode, index, &inputs[1],
607 &inputs[2])) {
608 input_count = 3;
609 } else {
610 inputs[1] = g.UseRegister(index);
611 if (opcode == kArmVld1S128) {
612 EmitAddBeforeS128LoadStore(selector, &opcode, &input_count, &inputs[0]);
613 } else {
614 opcode |= AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_Offset_RR);
615 }
616 }
617 selector->Emit(opcode, 1, output, input_count, inputs);
618}
619
620void EmitLoad(InstructionSelectorT<TurbofanAdapter>* selector,
621 InstructionCode opcode, InstructionOperand* output, Node* base,
622 Node* index) {
623 ArmOperandGeneratorT<TurbofanAdapter> g(selector);
624 InstructionOperand inputs[3];
625 size_t input_count = 2;
626
627 ExternalReferenceMatcher m(base);
628 if (m.HasResolvedValue() &&
629 selector->CanAddressRelativeToRootsRegister(m.ResolvedValue())) {
630 Int32Matcher int_matcher(index);
631 if (int_matcher.HasResolvedValue()) {
632 ptrdiff_t const delta =
633 int_matcher.ResolvedValue() +
634 MacroAssemblerBase::RootRegisterOffsetForExternalReference(
635 selector->isolate(), m.ResolvedValue());
636 input_count = 1;
637 inputs[0] = g.UseImmediate(static_cast<int32_t>(delta));
638 opcode |= AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_Root);
639 selector->Emit(opcode, 1, output, input_count, inputs);
640 return;
641 }
642 }
643
644 if (base->opcode() == IrOpcode::kLoadRootRegister) {
645 input_count = 1;
646 // This will only work if {index} is a constant.
647 inputs[0] = g.UseImmediate(index);
648 opcode |= AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_Root);
649 selector->Emit(opcode, 1, output, input_count, inputs);
650 return;
651 }
652
653 inputs[0] = g.UseRegister(base);
654 if (g.CanBeImmediate(index, opcode)) {
655 inputs[1] = g.UseImmediate(index);
656 opcode |= AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_Offset_RI);
657 } else if ((opcode == kArmLdr) &&
658 TryMatchLSLImmediate(selector, &opcode, index, &inputs[1],
659 &inputs[2])) {
660 input_count = 3;
661 } else {
662 inputs[1] = g.UseRegister(index);
663 if (opcode == kArmVld1S128) {
664 EmitAddBeforeS128LoadStore(selector, &opcode, &input_count, &inputs[0]);
665 } else {
666 opcode |= AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_Offset_RR);
667 }
668 }
669 selector->Emit(opcode, 1, output, input_count, inputs);
670}
671
672template <typename Adapter>
673void EmitStore(InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>* selector, InstructionCode opcode,
674 size_t input_count, InstructionOperand* inputs,
675 typename Adapter::node_t index) {
676 ArmOperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(selector);
677 ArchOpcode arch_opcode = ArchOpcodeField::decode(opcode);
678
679 if (g.CanBeImmediate(index, opcode)) {
680 inputs[input_count++] = g.UseImmediate(index);
681 opcode |= AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_Offset_RI);
682 } else if ((arch_opcode == kArmStr || arch_opcode == kAtomicStoreWord32) &&
683 TryMatchLSLImmediate(selector, &opcode, index, &inputs[2],
684 &inputs[3])) {
685 input_count = 4;
686 } else {
687 inputs[input_count++] = g.UseRegister(index);
688 if (arch_opcode == kArmVst1S128) {
689 // Inputs are value, base, index, only care about base and index.
690 EmitAddBeforeS128LoadStore(selector, &opcode, &input_count, &inputs[1]);
691 } else {
692 opcode |= AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_Offset_RR);
693 }
694 }
695 selector->Emit(opcode, 0, nullptr, input_count, inputs);
696}
697
698template <typename Adapter>
699void VisitPairAtomicBinOp(InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>* selector,
700 typename Adapter::node_t node, ArchOpcode opcode) {
701 ArmOperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(selector);
702 using node_t = typename Adapter::node_t;
703 node_t base = selector->input_at(node, 0);
704 node_t index = selector->input_at(node, 1);
705 node_t value = selector->input_at(node, 2);
706 node_t value_high = selector->input_at(node, 3);
707 AddressingMode addressing_mode = kMode_Offset_RR;
708 InstructionCode code = opcode | AddressingModeField::encode(addressing_mode);
709 InstructionOperand inputs[] = {
710 g.UseUniqueRegister(value), g.UseUniqueRegister(value_high),
711 g.UseUniqueRegister(base), g.UseUniqueRegister(index)};
712 InstructionOperand outputs[2];
713 size_t output_count = 0;
714 InstructionOperand temps[6];
715 size_t temp_count = 0;
716 temps[temp_count++] = g.TempRegister();
717 temps[temp_count++] = g.TempRegister(r6);
718 temps[temp_count++] = g.TempRegister(r7);
719 temps[temp_count++] = g.TempRegister();
720 node_t projection0 = selector->FindProjection(node, 0);
721 node_t projection1 = selector->FindProjection(node, 1);
722 if (selector->valid(projection0)) {
723 outputs[output_count++] = g.DefineAsFixed(projection0, r2);
724 } else {
725 temps[temp_count++] = g.TempRegister(r2);
726 }
727 if (selector->valid(projection1)) {
728 outputs[output_count++] = g.DefineAsFixed(projection1, r3);
729 } else {
730 temps[temp_count++] = g.TempRegister(r3);
731 }
732 selector->Emit(code, output_count, outputs, arraysize(inputs), inputs,
733 temp_count, temps);
734}

968template <typename Adapter>
969void InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>::VisitLoad(node_t node) {
970 typename Adapter::LoadView load = this->load_view(node);
971 LoadRepresentation load_rep = load.loaded_rep();
972 ArmOperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(this);
973 node_t base = load.base();
974 node_t index = load.index();
975
976 InstructionCode opcode = kArchNop;
977 switch (load_rep.representation()) {
978 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat32:
979 opcode = kArmVldrF32;
980 break;
981 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat64:
982 opcode = kArmVldrF64;
983 break;
984 case MachineRepresentation::kBit: // Fall through.
985 case MachineRepresentation::kWord8:
986 opcode = load_rep.IsUnsigned() ? kArmLdrb : kArmLdrsb;
987 break;
988 case MachineRepresentation::kWord16:
989 opcode = load_rep.IsUnsigned() ? kArmLdrh : kArmLdrsh;
990 break;
991 case MachineRepresentation::kTaggedSigned: // Fall through.
992 case MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer: // Fall through.
993 case MachineRepresentation::kTagged: // Fall through.
994 case MachineRepresentation::kWord32:
995 opcode = kArmLdr;
996 break;
997 case MachineRepresentation::kSimd128:
998 opcode = kArmVld1S128;
999 break;
1000 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat16:
1001 UNIMPLEMENTED();
1002 case MachineRepresentation::kSimd256: // Fall through.
1003 case MachineRepresentation::kCompressedPointer: // Fall through.
1004 case MachineRepresentation::kCompressed: // Fall through.
1005 case MachineRepresentation::kProtectedPointer: // Fall through.
1006 case MachineRepresentation::kIndirectPointer: // Fall through.
1007 case MachineRepresentation::kSandboxedPointer: // Fall through.
1008 case MachineRepresentation::kWord64: // Fall through.
1009 case MachineRepresentation::kMapWord: // Fall through.
1010 case MachineRepresentation::kNone:
1011 UNREACHABLE();
1012 }
1013
1014 InstructionOperand output = g.DefineAsRegister(node);
1015 EmitLoad(this, opcode, &output, base, index);
1016}

1075template <typename Adapter>
1076void VisitStoreCommon(InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>* selector,
1077 typename Adapter::node_t node,
1078 StoreRepresentation store_rep,
1079 std::optional<AtomicMemoryOrder> atomic_order) {
1080 using node_t = typename Adapter::node_t;
1081 ArmOperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(selector);
1082 auto store_view = selector->store_view(node);
1083 node_t base = store_view.base();
1084 node_t index = selector->value(store_view.index());
1085 node_t value = store_view.value();
1086
1087 WriteBarrierKind write_barrier_kind = store_rep.write_barrier_kind();
1088 MachineRepresentation rep = store_rep.representation();
1089
1090 if (v8_flags.enable_unconditional_write_barriers && CanBeTaggedPointer(rep)) {
1091 write_barrier_kind = kFullWriteBarrier;
1092 }
1093
1094 if (write_barrier_kind != kNoWriteBarrier &&
1095 !v8_flags.disable_write_barriers) {
1096 DCHECK(CanBeTaggedPointer(rep));
1097 AddressingMode addressing_mode;
1098 InstructionOperand inputs[3];
1099 size_t input_count = 0;
1100 inputs[input_count++] = g.UseUniqueRegister(base);
1101 // OutOfLineRecordWrite uses the index in an 'add' instruction as well as
1102 // for the store itself, so we must check compatibility with both.
1103 if (g.CanBeImmediate(index, kArmAdd) && g.CanBeImmediate(index, kArmStr)) {
1104 inputs[input_count++] = g.UseImmediate(index);
1105 addressing_mode = kMode_Offset_RI;
1106 } else {
1107 inputs[input_count++] = g.UseUniqueRegister(index);
1108 addressing_mode = kMode_Offset_RR;
1109 }
1110 inputs[input_count++] = g.UseUniqueRegister(value);
1111 RecordWriteMode record_write_mode =
1112 WriteBarrierKindToRecordWriteMode(write_barrier_kind);
1113 InstructionCode code;
1114 if (!atomic_order) {
1115 code = kArchStoreWithWriteBarrier;
1116 code |= RecordWriteModeField::encode(record_write_mode);
1117 } else {
1118 code = kArchAtomicStoreWithWriteBarrier;
1119 code |= AtomicMemoryOrderField::encode(*atomic_order);
1120 code |= AtomicStoreRecordWriteModeField::encode(record_write_mode);
1121 }
1122 code |= AddressingModeField::encode(addressing_mode);
1123 selector->Emit(code, 0, nullptr, input_count, inputs);
1124 } else {
1125 InstructionCode opcode = kArchNop;
1126 if (!atomic_order) {
1127 opcode = GetStoreOpcode(rep);
1128 } else {
1129 // Release stores emit DMB ISH; STR while sequentially consistent stores
1130 // emit DMB ISH; STR; DMB ISH.
1131 // https://www.cl.cam.ac.uk/~pes20/cpp/cpp0xmappings.html
1132 opcode = GetAtomicStoreOpcode(rep);
1133 opcode |= AtomicMemoryOrderField::encode(*atomic_order);
1134 }
1135
1136 std::optional<ExternalReference> external_base;
1137 if constexpr (Adapter::IsTurboshaft) {
1138 ExternalReference value;
1139 if (selector->MatchExternalConstant(store_view.base(), &value)) {
1140 external_base = value;
1141 }
1142 } else {
1143 ExternalReferenceMatcher m(store_view.base());
1144 if (m.HasResolvedValue()) {
1145 external_base = m.ResolvedValue();
1146 }
1147 }
1148
1149 if (external_base &&
1150 selector->CanAddressRelativeToRootsRegister(*external_base)) {
1151 if (selector->is_integer_constant(index)) {
1152 ptrdiff_t const delta =
1153 selector->integer_constant(index) +
1154 MacroAssemblerBase::RootRegisterOffsetForExternalReference(
1155 selector->isolate(), *external_base);
1156 int input_count = 2;
1157 InstructionOperand inputs[2];
1158 inputs[0] = g.UseRegister(value);
1159 inputs[1] = g.UseImmediate(static_cast<int32_t>(delta));
1160 opcode |= AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_Root);
1161 selector->Emit(opcode, 0, nullptr, input_count, inputs);
1162 return;
1163 }
1164 }
1165
1166 if (selector->is_load_root_register(base)) {
1167 int input_count = 2;
1168 InstructionOperand inputs[2];
1169 inputs[0] = g.UseRegister(value);
1170 inputs[1] = g.UseImmediate(index);
1171 opcode |= AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_Root);
1172 selector->Emit(opcode, 0, nullptr, input_count, inputs);
1173 return;
1174 }
1175
1176 InstructionOperand inputs[4];
1177 size_t input_count = 0;
1178 inputs[input_count++] = g.UseRegister(value);
1179 inputs[input_count++] = g.UseRegister(base);
1180 EmitStore(selector, opcode, input_count, inputs, index);
1181 }
1182}

1203template <typename Adapter>
1204void InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>::VisitUnalignedLoad(node_t node) {
1205 auto load = this->load_view(node);
1206 MachineRepresentation load_rep = load.loaded_rep().representation();
1207 ArmOperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(this);
1208 node_t base = this->input_at(node, 0);
1209 node_t index = this->input_at(node, 1);
1210
1211 InstructionCode opcode = kArmLdr;
1212 // Only floating point loads need to be specially handled; integer loads
1213 // support unaligned access. We support unaligned FP loads by loading to
1214 // integer registers first, then moving to the destination FP register. If
1215 // NEON is supported, we use the vld1.8 instruction.
1216 switch (load_rep) {
1217 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat32: {
1218 InstructionOperand temp = g.TempRegister();
1219 EmitLoad(this, opcode, &temp, base, index);
1220 Emit(kArmVmovF32U32, g.DefineAsRegister(node), temp);
1221 return;
1222 }
1223 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat64: {
1224 // Compute the address of the least-significant byte of the FP value.
1225 // We assume that the base node is unlikely to be an encodable immediate
1226 // or the result of a shift operation, so only consider the addressing
1227 // mode that should be used for the index node.
1228 InstructionCode add_opcode = kArmAdd;
1229 InstructionOperand inputs[3];
1230 inputs[0] = g.UseRegister(base);
1231
1232 size_t input_count;
1233 if (TryMatchImmediateOrShift(this, &add_opcode, index, &input_count,
1234 &inputs[1])) {
1235 // input_count has been set by TryMatchImmediateOrShift(), so
1236 // increment it to account for the base register in inputs[0].
1237 input_count++;
1238 } else {
1239 add_opcode |= AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_Operand2_R);
1240 inputs[1] = g.UseRegister(index);
1241 input_count = 2; // Base register and index.
1242 }
1243
1244 InstructionOperand addr = g.TempRegister();
1245 Emit(add_opcode, 1, &addr, input_count, inputs);
1246
1247 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(NEON)) {
1248 // With NEON we can load directly from the calculated address.
1249 InstructionCode op = kArmVld1F64;
1250 op |= AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_Operand2_R);
1251 Emit(op, g.DefineAsRegister(node), addr);
1252 } else {
1253 // Load both halves and move to an FP register.
1254 InstructionOperand fp_lo = g.TempRegister();
1255 InstructionOperand fp_hi = g.TempRegister();
1256 opcode |= AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_Offset_RI);
1257 Emit(opcode, fp_lo, addr, g.TempImmediate(0));
1258 Emit(opcode, fp_hi, addr, g.TempImmediate(4));
1259 Emit(kArmVmovF64U32U32, g.DefineAsRegister(node), fp_lo, fp_hi);
1260 }
1261 return;
1262 }
1263 default:
1264 // All other cases should support unaligned accesses.
1265 UNREACHABLE();
1266 }
1267}

1269template <typename Adapter>
1270void InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>::VisitUnalignedStore(node_t node) {
1271 ArmOperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(this);
1272 auto store_view = this->store_view(node);
1273 node_t base = store_view.base();
1274 node_t index = this->value(store_view.index());
1275 node_t value = store_view.value();
1276
1277 InstructionOperand inputs[4];
1278 size_t input_count = 0;
1279
1280 UnalignedStoreRepresentation store_rep =
1281 store_view.stored_rep().representation();
1282
1283 // Only floating point stores need to be specially handled; integer stores
1284 // support unaligned access. We support unaligned FP stores by moving the
1285 // value to integer registers first, then storing to the destination address.
1286 // If NEON is supported, we use the vst1.8 instruction.
1287 switch (store_rep) {
1288 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat32: {
1289 inputs[input_count++] = g.TempRegister();
1290 Emit(kArmVmovU32F32, inputs[0], g.UseRegister(value));
1291 inputs[input_count++] = g.UseRegister(base);
1292 EmitStore(this, kArmStr, input_count, inputs, index);
1293 return;
1294 }
1295 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat64: {
1296 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(NEON)) {
1297 InstructionOperand address = g.TempRegister();
1298 {
1299 // First we have to calculate the actual address.
1300 InstructionCode add_opcode = kArmAdd;
1301 InstructionOperand inputs[3];
1302 inputs[0] = g.UseRegister(base);
1303
1304 size_t input_count;
1305 if (TryMatchImmediateOrShift(this, &add_opcode, index, &input_count,
1306 &inputs[1])) {
1307 // input_count has been set by TryMatchImmediateOrShift(), so
1308 // increment it to account for the base register in inputs[0].
1309 input_count++;
1310 } else {
1311 add_opcode |= AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_Operand2_R);
1312 inputs[1] = g.UseRegister(index);
1313 input_count = 2; // Base register and index.
1314 }
1315
1316 Emit(add_opcode, 1, &address, input_count, inputs);
1317 }
1318
1319 inputs[input_count++] = g.UseRegister(value);
1320 inputs[input_count++] = address;
1321 InstructionCode op = kArmVst1F64;
1322 op |= AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_Operand2_R);
1323 Emit(op, 0, nullptr, input_count, inputs);
1324 } else {
1325 // Store a 64-bit floating point value using two 32-bit integer stores.
1326 // Computing the store address here would require three live temporary
1327 // registers (fp<63:32>, fp<31:0>, address), so compute base + 4 after
1328 // storing the least-significant half of the value.
1329
1330 // First, move the 64-bit FP value into two temporary integer registers.
1331 InstructionOperand fp[] = {g.TempRegister(), g.TempRegister()};
1332 inputs[input_count++] = g.UseRegister(value);
1333 Emit(kArmVmovU32U32F64, arraysize(fp), fp, input_count, inputs);
1334
1335 // Store the least-significant half.
1336 inputs[0] = fp[0]; // Low 32-bits of FP value.
1337 inputs[input_count++] =
1338 g.UseRegister(base); // First store base address.
1339 EmitStore(this, kArmStr, input_count, inputs, index);
1340
1341 // Store the most-significant half.
1342 InstructionOperand base4 = g.TempRegister();
1343 Emit(kArmAdd | AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_Operand2_I), base4,
1344 g.UseRegister(base), g.TempImmediate(4)); // Compute base + 4.
1345 inputs[0] = fp[1]; // High 32-bits of FP value.
1346 inputs[1] = base4; // Second store base + 4 address.
1347 EmitStore(this, kArmStr, input_count, inputs, index);
1348 }
1349 return;
1350 }
1351 default:
1352 // All other cases should support unaligned accesses.
1353 UNREACHABLE();
1354 }
1355}

1359template <typename Adapter>
1360void EmitBic(InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>* selector,
1361 typename Adapter::node_t node, typename Adapter::node_t left,
1362 typename Adapter::node_t right) {
1363 ArmOperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(selector);
1364 InstructionCode opcode = kArmBic;
1365 InstructionOperand value_operand;
1366 InstructionOperand shift_operand;
1367 if (TryMatchShift(selector, &opcode, right, &value_operand, &shift_operand)) {
1368 selector->Emit(opcode, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(left),
1369 value_operand, shift_operand);
1370 return;
1371 }
1372 selector->Emit(opcode | AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_Operand2_R),
1373 g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(left),
1374 g.UseRegister(right));
1375}
1376
1377template <typename Adapter>
1378void EmitUbfx(InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>* selector,
1379 typename Adapter::node_t node, typename Adapter::node_t left,
1380 uint32_t lsb, uint32_t width) {
1381 DCHECK_LE(lsb, 31u);
1382 DCHECK_LE(1u, width);
1383 DCHECK_LE(width, 32u - lsb);
1384 ArmOperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(selector);
1385 selector->Emit(kArmUbfx, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(left),
1386 g.TempImmediate(lsb), g.TempImmediate(width));
1387}

1391template <>
1392void InstructionSelectorT<TurboshaftAdapter>::VisitWord32And(node_t node) {
1393 using namespace turboshaft; // NOLINT(build/namespaces)
1394 ArmOperandGeneratorT<TurboshaftAdapter> g(this);
1395
1396 const WordBinopOp& bitwise_and = Get(node).Cast<WordBinopOp>();
1397 const Operation& lhs = Get(bitwise_and.left());
1398
1399 if (lhs.Is<Opmask::kWord32BitwiseXor>() &&
1400 CanCover(node, bitwise_and.left())) {
1401 const WordBinopOp& bitwise_xor = lhs.Cast<WordBinopOp>();
1402 int32_t bitmask;
1403 if (MatchIntegralWord32Constant(bitwise_xor.right(), &bitmask) &&
1404 bitmask == -1) {
1405 EmitBic(this, node, bitwise_and.right(), bitwise_xor.left());
1406 return;
1407 }
1408 }
1409
1410 const Operation& rhs = Get(bitwise_and.right());
1411 if (rhs.Is<Opmask::kWord32BitwiseXor>() &&
1412 CanCover(node, bitwise_and.right())) {
1413 const WordBinopOp& bitwise_xor = rhs.Cast<WordBinopOp>();
1414 int32_t bitmask;
1415 if (MatchIntegralWord32Constant(bitwise_xor.right(), &bitmask) &&
1416 bitmask == -1) {
1417 EmitBic(this, node, bitwise_and.left(), bitwise_xor.left());
1418 return;
1419 }
1420 }
1421
1422 if (is_integer_constant(bitwise_and.right())) {
1423 uint32_t const value = integer_constant(bitwise_and.right());
1424 uint32_t width = base::bits::CountPopulation(value);
1425 uint32_t leading_zeros = base::bits::CountLeadingZeros32(value);
1426
1427 // Try to merge SHR operations on the left hand input into this AND.
1428 if (lhs.Is<Opmask::kWord32ShiftRightLogical>()) {
1429 const ShiftOp& shr = lhs.Cast<ShiftOp>();
1430 if (is_integer_constant(shr.right())) {
1431 uint32_t const shift = integer_constant(shr.right());
1432
1433 if (((shift == 8) || (shift == 16) || (shift == 24)) &&
1434 (value == 0xFF)) {
1435 // Merge SHR into AND by emitting a UXTB instruction with a
1436 // bytewise rotation.
1437 Emit(kArmUxtb, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(shr.left()),
1438 g.TempImmediate(shift));
1439 return;
1440 } else if (((shift == 8) || (shift == 16)) && (value == 0xFFFF)) {
1441 // Merge SHR into AND by emitting a UXTH instruction with a
1442 // bytewise rotation.
1443 Emit(kArmUxth, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(shr.left()),
1444 g.TempImmediate(shift));
1445 return;
1446 } else if (IsSupported(ARMv7) && (width != 0) &&
1447 ((leading_zeros + width) == 32)) {
1448 // Merge Shr into And by emitting a UBFX instruction.
1449 DCHECK_EQ(0u, base::bits::CountTrailingZeros32(value));
1450 if ((1 <= shift) && (shift <= 31)) {
1451 // UBFX cannot extract bits past the register size, however since
1452 // shifting the original value would have introduced some zeros we
1453 // can still use UBFX with a smaller mask and the remaining bits
1454 // will be zeros.
1455 EmitUbfx(this, node, shr.left(), shift,
1456 std::min(width, 32 - shift));
1457 return;
1458 }
1459 }
1460 }
1461 } else if (value == 0xFFFF) {
1462 // Emit UXTH for this AND. We don't bother testing for UXTB, as it's no
1463 // better than AND 0xFF for this operation.
1464 Emit(kArmUxth, g.DefineAsRegister(node),
1465 g.UseRegister(bitwise_and.left()), g.TempImmediate(0));
1466 return;
1467 }
1468 if (g.CanBeImmediate(~value)) {
1469 // Emit BIC for this AND by inverting the immediate value first.
1470 Emit(kArmBic | AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_Operand2_I),
1471 g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(bitwise_and.left()),
1472 g.TempImmediate(~value));
1473 return;
1474 }
1475 if (!g.CanBeImmediate(value) && IsSupported(ARMv7)) {
1476 // If value has 9 to 23 contiguous set bits, and has the lsb set, we can
1477 // replace this AND with UBFX. Other contiguous bit patterns have
1478 // already been handled by BIC or will be handled by AND.
1479 if ((width != 0) && ((leading_zeros + width) == 32) &&
1480 (9 <= leading_zeros) && (leading_zeros <= 23)) {
1481 DCHECK_EQ(0u, base::bits::CountTrailingZeros32(value));
1482 EmitUbfx(this, node, bitwise_and.left(), 0, width);
1483 return;
1484 }
1485
1486 width = 32 - width;
1487 leading_zeros = base::bits::CountLeadingZeros32(~value);
1488 uint32_t lsb = base::bits::CountTrailingZeros32(~value);
1489 if ((leading_zeros + width + lsb) == 32) {
1490 // This AND can be replaced with BFC.
1491 Emit(kArmBfc, g.DefineSameAsFirst(node),
1492 g.UseRegister(bitwise_and.left()), g.TempImmediate(lsb),
1493 g.TempImmediate(width));
1494 return;
1495 }
1496 }
1497 }
1498 VisitBinop(this, node, kArmAnd, kArmAnd);
1499}

1501template <typename Adapter>
1502void InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>::VisitWord32And(node_t node) {
1503 ArmOperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(this);
1504 Int32BinopMatcher m(node);
1505 if (m.left().IsWord32Xor() && CanCover(node, m.left().node())) {
1506 Int32BinopMatcher mleft(m.left().node());
1507 if (mleft.right().Is(-1)) {
1508 EmitBic(this, node, m.right().node(), mleft.left().node());
1509 return;
1510 }
1511 }
1512 if (m.right().IsWord32Xor() && CanCover(node, m.right().node())) {
1513 Int32BinopMatcher mright(m.right().node());
1514 if (mright.right().Is(-1)) {
1515 EmitBic(this, node, m.left().node(), mright.left().node());
1516 return;
1517 }
1518 }
1519 if (m.right().HasResolvedValue()) {
1520 uint32_t const value = m.right().ResolvedValue();
1521 uint32_t width = base::bits::CountPopulation(value);
1522 uint32_t leading_zeros = base::bits::CountLeadingZeros32(value);
1523
1524 // Try to merge SHR operations on the left hand input into this AND.
1525 if (m.left().IsWord32Shr()) {
1526 Int32BinopMatcher mshr(m.left().node());
1527 if (mshr.right().HasResolvedValue()) {
1528 uint32_t const shift = mshr.right().ResolvedValue();
1529
1530 if (((shift == 8) || (shift == 16) || (shift == 24)) &&
1531 (value == 0xFF)) {
1532 // Merge SHR into AND by emitting a UXTB instruction with a
1533 // bytewise rotation.
1534 Emit(kArmUxtb, g.DefineAsRegister(m.node()),
1535 g.UseRegister(mshr.left().node()),
1536 g.TempImmediate(mshr.right().ResolvedValue()));
1537 return;
1538 } else if (((shift == 8) || (shift == 16)) && (value == 0xFFFF)) {
1539 // Merge SHR into AND by emitting a UXTH instruction with a
1540 // bytewise rotation.
1541 Emit(kArmUxth, g.DefineAsRegister(m.node()),
1542 g.UseRegister(mshr.left().node()),
1543 g.TempImmediate(mshr.right().ResolvedValue()));
1544 return;
1545 } else if (IsSupported(ARMv7) && (width != 0) &&
1546 ((leading_zeros + width) == 32)) {
1547 // Merge Shr into And by emitting a UBFX instruction.
1548 DCHECK_EQ(0u, base::bits::CountTrailingZeros32(value));
1549 if ((1 <= shift) && (shift <= 31)) {
1550 // UBFX cannot extract bits past the register size, however since
1551 // shifting the original value would have introduced some zeros we
1552 // can still use UBFX with a smaller mask and the remaining bits
1553 // will be zeros.
1554 EmitUbfx(this, node, mshr.left().node(), shift,
1555 std::min(width, 32 - shift));
1556 return;
1557 }
1558 }
1559 }
1560 } else if (value == 0xFFFF) {
1561 // Emit UXTH for this AND. We don't bother testing for UXTB, as it's no
1562 // better than AND 0xFF for this operation.
1563 Emit(kArmUxth, g.DefineAsRegister(m.node()),
1564 g.UseRegister(m.left().node()), g.TempImmediate(0));
1565 return;
1566 }
1567 if (g.CanBeImmediate(~value)) {
1568 // Emit BIC for this AND by inverting the immediate value first.
1569 Emit(kArmBic | AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_Operand2_I),
1570 g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(m.left().node()),
1571 g.TempImmediate(~value));
1572 return;
1573 }
1574 if (!g.CanBeImmediate(value) && IsSupported(ARMv7)) {
1575 // If value has 9 to 23 contiguous set bits, and has the lsb set, we can
1576 // replace this AND with UBFX. Other contiguous bit patterns have
1577 // already been handled by BIC or will be handled by AND.
1578 if ((width != 0) && ((leading_zeros + width) == 32) &&
1579 (9 <= leading_zeros) && (leading_zeros <= 23)) {
1580 DCHECK_EQ(0u, base::bits::CountTrailingZeros32(value));
1581 EmitUbfx(this, node, m.left().node(), 0, width);
1582 return;
1583 }
1584
1585 width = 32 - width;
1586 leading_zeros = base::bits::CountLeadingZeros32(~value);
1587 uint32_t lsb = base::bits::CountTrailingZeros32(~value);
1588 if ((leading_zeros + width + lsb) == 32) {
1589 // This AND can be replaced with BFC.
1590 Emit(kArmBfc, g.DefineSameAsFirst(node),
1591 g.UseRegister(m.left().node()), g.TempImmediate(lsb),
1592 g.TempImmediate(width));
1593 return;
1594 }
1595 }
1596 }
1597 VisitBinop(this, node, kArmAnd, kArmAnd);
1598}

1605template <typename Adapter>
1606void InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>::VisitWord32Xor(node_t node) {
1607 ArmOperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(this);
1608 if constexpr (Adapter::IsTurboshaft) {
1609 using namespace turboshaft; // NOLINT(build/namespaces)
1610 const WordBinopOp& bitwise_xor =
1611 this->Get(node).template Cast<WordBinopOp>();
1612 int32_t mask;
1613 if (this->MatchIntegralWord32Constant(bitwise_xor.right(), &mask) &&
1614 mask == -1) {
1615 InstructionCode opcode = kArmMvn;
1616 InstructionOperand value_operand;
1617 InstructionOperand shift_operand;
1618 if (TryMatchShift(this, &opcode, bitwise_xor.left(), &value_operand,
1619 &shift_operand)) {
1620 Emit(opcode, g.DefineAsRegister(node), value_operand, shift_operand);
1621 return;
1622 }
1623 Emit(opcode | AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_Operand2_R),
1624 g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(bitwise_xor.left()));
1625 return;
1626 }
1627 VisitBinop(this, node, kArmEor, kArmEor);
1628 } else {
1629 Int32BinopMatcher m(node);
1630 if (m.right().Is(-1)) {
1631 InstructionCode opcode = kArmMvn;
1632 InstructionOperand value_operand;
1633 InstructionOperand shift_operand;
1634 if (TryMatchShift(this, &opcode, m.left().node(), &value_operand,
1635 &shift_operand)) {
1636 Emit(opcode, g.DefineAsRegister(node), value_operand, shift_operand);
1637 return;
1638 }
1639 Emit(opcode | AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_Operand2_R),
1640 g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(m.left().node()));
1641 return;
1642 }
1643 VisitBinop(this, node, kArmEor, kArmEor);
1644 }

1647template <typename Adapter>
1648void InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>::VisitStackPointerGreaterThan(
1649 node_t node, FlagsContinuation* cont) {
1650 StackCheckKind kind;
1651 node_t value;
1652 if constexpr (Adapter::IsTurboshaft) {
1653 const auto& op =
1654 this->turboshaft_graph()
1655 ->Get(node)
1656 .template Cast<turboshaft::StackPointerGreaterThanOp>();
1657 kind = op.kind;
1658 value = op.stack_limit();
1659 } else {
1660 kind = StackCheckKindOf(node->op());
1661 value = node->InputAt(0);
1662 }
1663 InstructionCode opcode =
1664 kArchStackPointerGreaterThan | MiscField::encode(static_cast<int>(kind));
1665
1666 ArmOperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(this);
1667
1668 // No outputs.
1669 InstructionOperand* const outputs = nullptr;
1670 const int output_count = 0;
1671
1672 // Applying an offset to this stack check requires a temp register. Offsets
1673 // are only applied to the first stack check. If applying an offset, we must
1674 // ensure the input and temp registers do not alias, thus kUniqueRegister.
1675 InstructionOperand temps[] = {g.TempRegister()};
1676 const int temp_count = (kind == StackCheckKind::kJSFunctionEntry) ? 1 : 0;
1677 const auto register_mode = (kind == StackCheckKind::kJSFunctionEntry)
1678 ? OperandGenerator::kUniqueRegister
1679 : OperandGenerator::kRegister;
1680
1681 InstructionOperand inputs[] = {g.UseRegisterWithMode(value, register_mode)};
1682 static constexpr int input_count = arraysize(inputs);
1683
1684 EmitWithContinuation(opcode, output_count, outputs, input_count, inputs,
1685 temp_count, temps, cont);
1686}

1690template <typename TryMatchShift, typename Adapter>
1691void VisitShift(InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>* selector,
1692 typename Adapter::node_t node, TryMatchShift try_match_shift,
1693 FlagsContinuationT<Adapter>* cont) {
1694 ArmOperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(selector);
1695 InstructionCode opcode = kArmMov;
1696 InstructionOperand inputs[2];
1697 size_t input_count = 2;
1698 InstructionOperand outputs[1];
1699 size_t output_count = 0;
1700
1701 CHECK(try_match_shift(selector, &opcode, node, &inputs[0], &inputs[1]));
1702
1703 outputs[output_count++] = g.DefineAsRegister(node);
1704
1705 DCHECK_NE(0u, input_count);
1706 DCHECK_NE(0u, output_count);
1707 DCHECK_GE(arraysize(inputs), input_count);
1708 DCHECK_GE(arraysize(outputs), output_count);
1709 DCHECK_NE(kMode_None, AddressingModeField::decode(opcode));
1710
1711 selector->EmitWithContinuation(opcode, output_count, outputs, input_count,
1712 inputs, cont);
1713}

1716void VisitShift(InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>* selector,
1717 typename Adapter::node_t node, TryMatchShift try_match_shift) {
1718 FlagsContinuationT<Adapter> cont;
1719 VisitShift(selector, node, try_match_shift, &cont);
1720}

1729template <typename Adapter>
1730void InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>::VisitWord32Shr(node_t node) {
1731 ArmOperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(this);
1732 if constexpr (Adapter::IsTurboshaft) {
1733 using namespace turboshaft; // NOLINT(build/namespaces)
1734 const ShiftOp& shr = this->Get(node).template Cast<ShiftOp>();
1735 const Operation& lhs = this->Get(shr.left());
1736 if (IsSupported(ARMv7) && lhs.Is<Opmask::kWord32BitwiseAnd>() &&
1737 this->is_integer_constant(shr.right()) &&
1738 base::IsInRange(this->integer_constant(shr.right()), 0, 31)) {
1739 uint32_t lsb = this->integer_constant(shr.right());
1740 const WordBinopOp& bitwise_and = lhs.Cast<WordBinopOp>();
1741 if (this->is_integer_constant(bitwise_and.right())) {
1742 uint32_t value = static_cast<uint32_t>(
1743 this->integer_constant(bitwise_and.right())) >>
1744 lsb << lsb;
1745 uint32_t width = base::bits::CountPopulation(value);
1746 uint32_t msb = base::bits::CountLeadingZeros32(value);
1747 if ((width != 0) && (msb + width + lsb == 32)) {
1748 DCHECK_EQ(lsb, base::bits::CountTrailingZeros32(value));
1749 return EmitUbfx(this, node, bitwise_and.left(), lsb, width);
1750 }
1751 }
1752 }
1753 VisitShift(this, node, TryMatchLSR<Adapter>);
1754 } else {
1755 Int32BinopMatcher m(node);
1756 if (IsSupported(ARMv7) && m.left().IsWord32And() &&
1757 m.right().IsInRange(0, 31)) {
1758 uint32_t lsb = m.right().ResolvedValue();
1759 Int32BinopMatcher mleft(m.left().node());
1760 if (mleft.right().HasResolvedValue()) {
1761 uint32_t value =
1762 static_cast<uint32_t>(mleft.right().ResolvedValue() >> lsb) << lsb;
1763 uint32_t width = base::bits::CountPopulation(value);
1764 uint32_t msb = base::bits::CountLeadingZeros32(value);
1765 if ((width != 0) && (msb + width + lsb == 32)) {
1766 DCHECK_EQ(lsb, base::bits::CountTrailingZeros32(value));
1767 return EmitUbfx(this, node, mleft.left().node(), lsb, width);
1768 }
1769 }
1770 }
1771 VisitShift(this, node, TryMatchLSR<Adapter>);
1772 }
1773}
1774
1775template <typename Adapter>
1776void InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>::VisitWord32Sar(node_t node) {
1777 ArmOperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(this);
1778 if constexpr (Adapter::IsTurboshaft) {
1779 using namespace turboshaft; // NOLINT(build/namespaces)
1780 const ShiftOp& sar = this->Get(node).template Cast<ShiftOp>();
1781 const Operation& lhs = this->Get(sar.left());
1782 if (CanCover(node, sar.left()) && lhs.Is<Opmask::kWord32ShiftLeft>()) {
1783 const ShiftOp& shl = lhs.Cast<ShiftOp>();
1784 if (this->is_integer_constant(sar.right()) &&
1785 this->is_integer_constant(shl.right())) {
1786 uint32_t sar_by = this->integer_constant(sar.right());
1787 uint32_t shl_by = this->integer_constant(shl.right());
1788 if ((sar_by == shl_by) && (sar_by == 16)) {
1789 Emit(kArmSxth, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(shl.left()),
1790 g.TempImmediate(0));
1791 return;
1792 } else if ((sar_by == shl_by) && (sar_by == 24)) {
1793 Emit(kArmSxtb, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(shl.left()),
1794 g.TempImmediate(0));
1795 return;
1796 } else if (IsSupported(ARMv7) && (sar_by >= shl_by)) {
1797 Emit(kArmSbfx, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(shl.left()),
1798 g.TempImmediate(sar_by - shl_by), g.TempImmediate(32 - sar_by));
1799 return;
1800 }
1801 }
1802 }
1803 VisitShift(this, node, TryMatchASR<Adapter>);
1804 } else {
1805 Int32BinopMatcher m(node);
1806 if (CanCover(m.node(), m.left().node()) && m.left().IsWord32Shl()) {
1807 Int32BinopMatcher mleft(m.left().node());
1808 if (m.right().HasResolvedValue() && mleft.right().HasResolvedValue()) {
1809 uint32_t sar = m.right().ResolvedValue();
1810 uint32_t shl = mleft.right().ResolvedValue();
1811 if ((sar == shl) && (sar == 16)) {
1812 Emit(kArmSxth, g.DefineAsRegister(node),
1813 g.UseRegister(mleft.left().node()), g.TempImmediate(0));
1814 return;
1815 } else if ((sar == shl) && (sar == 24)) {
1816 Emit(kArmSxtb, g.DefineAsRegister(node),
1817 g.UseRegister(mleft.left().node()), g.TempImmediate(0));
1818 return;
1819 } else if (IsSupported(ARMv7) && (sar >= shl)) {
1820 Emit(kArmSbfx, g.DefineAsRegister(node),
1821 g.UseRegister(mleft.left().node()), g.TempImmediate(sar - shl),
1822 g.TempImmediate(32 - sar));
1823 return;
1824 }
1825 }
1826 }
1827 VisitShift(this, node, TryMatchASR<Adapter>);
1828 }

1831template <typename Adapter>
1832void InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>::VisitInt32PairAdd(node_t node) {
1833 ArmOperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(this);
1834
1835 node_t projection1 = this->FindProjection(node, 1);
1836 if (this->valid(projection1)) {
1837 // We use UseUniqueRegister here to avoid register sharing with the output
1838 // registers.
1839 InstructionOperand inputs[] = {
1840 g.UseRegister(this->input_at(node, 0)),
1841 g.UseUniqueRegister(this->input_at(node, 1)),
1842 g.UseRegister(this->input_at(node, 2)),
1843 g.UseUniqueRegister(this->input_at(node, 3))};
1844
1845 InstructionOperand outputs[] = {g.DefineAsRegister(node),
1846 g.DefineAsRegister(projection1)};
1847
1848 Emit(kArmAddPair, 2, outputs, 4, inputs);
1849 } else {
1850 // The high word of the result is not used, so we emit the standard 32 bit
1851 // instruction.
1852 Emit(kArmAdd | AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_Operand2_R),
1853 g.DefineSameAsFirst(node), g.UseRegister(this->input_at(node, 0)),
1854 g.UseRegister(this->input_at(node, 2)));
1855 }

1909namespace {
1910// Shared routine for multiple shift operations.
1911template <typename Adapter>
1912void VisitWord32PairShift(InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>* selector,
1913 InstructionCode opcode,
1914 typename Adapter::node_t node) {
1915 ArmOperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(selector);
1916 // We use g.UseUniqueRegister here to guarantee that there is
1917 // no register aliasing of input registers with output registers.
1918 InstructionOperand shift_operand;
1919 typename Adapter::node_t shift_by = selector->input_at(node, 2);
1920 if (selector->is_integer_constant(shift_by)) {
1921 shift_operand = g.UseImmediate(shift_by);
1922 } else {
1923 shift_operand = g.UseUniqueRegister(shift_by);
1924 }
1925
1926 InstructionOperand inputs[] = {
1927 g.UseUniqueRegister(selector->input_at(node, 0)),
1928 g.UseUniqueRegister(selector->input_at(node, 1)), shift_operand};
1929
1930 typename Adapter::node_t projection1 = selector->FindProjection(node, 1);
1931
1932 InstructionOperand outputs[2];
1933 InstructionOperand temps[1];
1934 int32_t output_count = 0;
1935 int32_t temp_count = 0;
1936
1937 outputs[output_count++] = g.DefineAsRegister(node);
1938 if (selector->valid(projection1)) {
1939 outputs[output_count++] = g.DefineAsRegister(projection1);
1940 } else {
1941 temps[temp_count++] = g.TempRegister();
1942 }
1943
1944 selector->Emit(opcode, output_count, outputs, 3, inputs, temp_count, temps);
1945}

2003template <>
2004void InstructionSelectorT<TurboshaftAdapter>::VisitInt32Add(node_t node) {
2005 using namespace turboshaft; // NOLINT(build/namespaces)
2006 ArmOperandGeneratorT<TurboshaftAdapter> g(this);
2007 const WordBinopOp& add = this->Get(node).Cast<WordBinopOp>();
2008 DCHECK(add.Is<Opmask::kWord32Add>());
2009 const Operation& left = this->Get(add.left());
2010
2011 if (CanCover(node, add.left())) {
2012 if (left.Is<Opmask::kWord32Mul>()) {
2013 const WordBinopOp& mul = left.Cast<WordBinopOp>();
2014 Emit(kArmMla, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(mul.left()),
2015 g.UseRegister(mul.right()), g.UseRegister(add.right()));
2016 return;
2017 }
2018 if (left.Is<Opmask::kWord32SignedMulOverflownBits>()) {
2019 const WordBinopOp& mul = left.Cast<WordBinopOp>();
2020 Emit(kArmSmmla, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(mul.left()),
2021 g.UseRegister(mul.right()), g.UseRegister(add.right()));
2022 return;
2023 }
2024 if (left.Is<Opmask::kWord32BitwiseAnd>()) {
2025 const WordBinopOp& bitwise_and = left.Cast<WordBinopOp>();
2026 uint32_t mask;
2027 if (MatchIntegralWord32Constant(bitwise_and.right(), &mask)) {
2028 if (mask == 0xFF) {
2029 Emit(kArmUxtab, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(add.right()),
2030 g.UseRegister(bitwise_and.left()), g.TempImmediate(0));
2031 return;
2032 } else if (mask == 0xFFFF) {
2033 Emit(kArmUxtah, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(add.right()),
2034 g.UseRegister(bitwise_and.left()), g.TempImmediate(0));
2035 return;
2036 }
2037 }
2038 } else if (left.Is<Opmask::kWord32ShiftRightArithmetic>()) {
2039 const ShiftOp& lhs_shift = left.Cast<ShiftOp>();
2040 if (CanCover(add.left(), lhs_shift.left()) &&
2041 Get(lhs_shift.left()).Is<Opmask::kWord32ShiftLeft>()) {
2042 const ShiftOp& lhs_shift_lhs_shift =
2043 Get(lhs_shift.left()).Cast<ShiftOp>();
2044 uint32_t sar_by, shl_by;
2045 if (MatchIntegralWord32Constant(lhs_shift.right(), &sar_by) &&
2046 MatchIntegralWord32Constant(lhs_shift_lhs_shift.right(), &shl_by)) {
2047 if (sar_by == 24 && shl_by == 24) {
2048 Emit(kArmSxtab, g.DefineAsRegister(node),
2049 g.UseRegister(add.right()),
2050 g.UseRegister(lhs_shift_lhs_shift.left()), g.TempImmediate(0));
2051 return;
2052 }
2053 if (sar_by == 16 && shl_by == 16) {
2054 Emit(kArmSxtah, g.DefineAsRegister(node),
2055 g.UseRegister(add.right()),
2056 g.UseRegister(lhs_shift_lhs_shift.left()), g.TempImmediate(0));
2057 return;
2058 }
2059 }
2060 }
2061 }
2062 }
2063
2064 const Operation& right = this->Get(add.right());
2065 if (CanCover(node, add.right())) {
2066 if (right.Is<Opmask::kWord32Mul>()) {
2067 const WordBinopOp& mul = right.Cast<WordBinopOp>();
2068 Emit(kArmMla, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(mul.left()),
2069 g.UseRegister(mul.right()), g.UseRegister(add.left()));
2070 return;
2071 }
2072 if (right.Is<Opmask::kWord32SignedMulOverflownBits>()) {
2073 const WordBinopOp& mul = right.Cast<WordBinopOp>();
2074 Emit(kArmSmmla, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(mul.left()),
2075 g.UseRegister(mul.right()), g.UseRegister(add.left()));
2076 return;
2077 }
2078 if (right.Is<Opmask::kWord32BitwiseAnd>()) {
2079 const WordBinopOp& bitwise_and = right.Cast<WordBinopOp>();
2080 uint32_t mask;
2081 if (MatchIntegralWord32Constant(bitwise_and.right(), &mask)) {
2082 if (mask == 0xFF) {
2083 Emit(kArmUxtab, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(add.left()),
2084 g.UseRegister(bitwise_and.left()), g.TempImmediate(0));
2085 return;
2086 } else if (mask == 0xFFFF) {
2087 Emit(kArmUxtah, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(add.left()),
2088 g.UseRegister(bitwise_and.left()), g.TempImmediate(0));
2089 return;
2090 }
2091 }
2092 } else if (right.Is<Opmask::kWord32ShiftRightArithmetic>()) {
2093 const ShiftOp& rhs_shift = right.Cast<ShiftOp>();
2094 if (CanCover(add.right(), rhs_shift.left()) &&
2095 Get(rhs_shift.left()).Is<Opmask::kWord32ShiftLeft>()) {
2096 const ShiftOp& rhs_shift_left = Get(rhs_shift.left()).Cast<ShiftOp>();
2097 uint32_t sar_by, shl_by;
2098 if (MatchIntegralWord32Constant(rhs_shift.right(), &sar_by) &&
2099 MatchIntegralWord32Constant(rhs_shift_left.right(), &shl_by)) {
2100 if (sar_by == 24 && shl_by == 24) {
2101 Emit(kArmSxtab, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(add.left()),
2102 g.UseRegister(rhs_shift_left.left()), g.TempImmediate(0));
2103 return;
2104 } else if (sar_by == 16 && shl_by == 16) {
2105 Emit(kArmSxtah, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(add.left()),
2106 g.UseRegister(rhs_shift_left.left()), g.TempImmediate(0));
2107 return;
2108 }
2109 }
2110 }
2111 }
2112 }
2113 VisitBinop(this, node, kArmAdd, kArmAdd);
2114}

2116template <>
2117void InstructionSelectorT<TurbofanAdapter>::VisitInt32Add(Node* node) {
2118 ArmOperandGeneratorT<TurbofanAdapter> g(this);
2119 Int32BinopMatcher m(node);
2120 if (CanCover(node, m.left().node())) {
2121 switch (m.left().opcode()) {
2122 case IrOpcode::kInt32Mul: {
2123 Int32BinopMatcher mleft(m.left().node());
2124 Emit(kArmMla, g.DefineAsRegister(node),
2125 g.UseRegister(mleft.left().node()),
2126 g.UseRegister(mleft.right().node()),
2127 g.UseRegister(m.right().node()));
2128 return;
2129 }
2130 case IrOpcode::kInt32MulHigh: {
2131 Int32BinopMatcher mleft(m.left().node());
2132 Emit(kArmSmmla, g.DefineAsRegister(node),
2133 g.UseRegister(mleft.left().node()),
2134 g.UseRegister(mleft.right().node()),
2135 g.UseRegister(m.right().node()));
2136 return;
2137 }
2138 case IrOpcode::kWord32And: {
2139 Int32BinopMatcher mleft(m.left().node());
2140 if (mleft.right().Is(0xFF)) {
2141 Emit(kArmUxtab, g.DefineAsRegister(node),
2142 g.UseRegister(m.right().node()),
2143 g.UseRegister(mleft.left().node()), g.TempImmediate(0));
2144 return;
2145 } else if (mleft.right().Is(0xFFFF)) {
2146 Emit(kArmUxtah, g.DefineAsRegister(node),
2147 g.UseRegister(m.right().node()),
2148 g.UseRegister(mleft.left().node()), g.TempImmediate(0));
2149 return;
2150 }
2151 break;
2152 }
2153 case IrOpcode::kWord32Sar: {
2154 Int32BinopMatcher mleft(m.left().node());
2155 if (CanCover(mleft.node(), mleft.left().node()) &&
2156 mleft.left().IsWord32Shl()) {
2157 Int32BinopMatcher mleftleft(mleft.left().node());
2158 if (mleft.right().Is(24) && mleftleft.right().Is(24)) {
2159 Emit(kArmSxtab, g.DefineAsRegister(node),
2160 g.UseRegister(m.right().node()),
2161 g.UseRegister(mleftleft.left().node()), g.TempImmediate(0));
2162 return;
2163 } else if (mleft.right().Is(16) && mleftleft.right().Is(16)) {
2164 Emit(kArmSxtah, g.DefineAsRegister(node),
2165 g.UseRegister(m.right().node()),
2166 g.UseRegister(mleftleft.left().node()), g.TempImmediate(0));
2167 return;
2168 }
2169 }
2170 break;
2171 }
2172 default:
2173 break;
2174 }
2175 }
2176 if (CanCover(node, m.right().node())) {
2177 switch (m.right().opcode()) {
2178 case IrOpcode::kInt32Mul: {
2179 Int32BinopMatcher mright(m.right().node());
2180 Emit(kArmMla, g.DefineAsRegister(node),
2181 g.UseRegister(mright.left().node()),
2182 g.UseRegister(mright.right().node()),
2183 g.UseRegister(m.left().node()));
2184 return;
2185 }
2186 case IrOpcode::kInt32MulHigh: {
2187 Int32BinopMatcher mright(m.right().node());
2188 Emit(kArmSmmla, g.DefineAsRegister(node),
2189 g.UseRegister(mright.left().node()),
2190 g.UseRegister(mright.right().node()),
2191 g.UseRegister(m.left().node()));
2192 return;
2193 }
2194 case IrOpcode::kWord32And: {
2195 Int32BinopMatcher mright(m.right().node());
2196 if (mright.right().Is(0xFF)) {
2197 Emit(kArmUxtab, g.DefineAsRegister(node),
2198 g.UseRegister(m.left().node()),
2199 g.UseRegister(mright.left().node()), g.TempImmediate(0));
2200 return;
2201 } else if (mright.right().Is(0xFFFF)) {
2202 Emit(kArmUxtah, g.DefineAsRegister(node),
2203 g.UseRegister(m.left().node()),
2204 g.UseRegister(mright.left().node()), g.TempImmediate(0));
2205 return;
2206 }
2207 break;
2208 }
2209 case IrOpcode::kWord32Sar: {
2210 Int32BinopMatcher mright(m.right().node());
2211 if (CanCover(mright.node(), mright.left().node()) &&
2212 mright.left().IsWord32Shl()) {
2213 Int32BinopMatcher mrightleft(mright.left().node());
2214 if (mright.right().Is(24) && mrightleft.right().Is(24)) {
2215 Emit(kArmSxtab, g.DefineAsRegister(node),
2216 g.UseRegister(m.left().node()),
2217 g.UseRegister(mrightleft.left().node()), g.TempImmediate(0));
2218 return;
2219 } else if (mright.right().Is(16) && mrightleft.right().Is(16)) {
2220 Emit(kArmSxtah, g.DefineAsRegister(node),
2221 g.UseRegister(m.left().node()),
2222 g.UseRegister(mrightleft.left().node()), g.TempImmediate(0));
2223 return;
2224 }
2225 }
2226 break;
2227 }
2228 default:
2229 break;
2230 }
2231 }
2232 VisitBinop(this, node, kArmAdd, kArmAdd);

2235template <typename Adapter>
2236void InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>::VisitInt32Sub(node_t node) {
2237 ArmOperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(this);
2238 if constexpr (Adapter::IsTurboshaft) {
2239 using namespace turboshaft; // NOLINT(build/namespaces)
2240 const WordBinopOp& sub = this->Get(node).template Cast<WordBinopOp>();
2241 const Operation& rhs = this->Get(sub.right());

2255 Emit(kArmMls, g.DefineAsRegister(node),
2256 g.UseRegister(mright.left().node()),
2257 g.UseRegister(mright.right().node()),
2258 g.UseRegister(m.left().node()));

2267template <typename Adapter>
2268void EmitInt32MulWithOverflow(InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>* selector,
2269 typename Adapter::node_t node,
2270 FlagsContinuationT<Adapter>* cont) {
2271 ArmOperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(selector);
2272 typename Adapter::node_t lhs = selector->input_at(node, 0);
2273 typename Adapter::node_t rhs = selector->input_at(node, 1);
2274 InstructionOperand result_operand = g.DefineAsRegister(node);
2275 InstructionOperand temp_operand = g.TempRegister();
2276 InstructionOperand outputs[] = {result_operand, temp_operand};
2277 InstructionOperand inputs[] = {g.UseRegister(lhs), g.UseRegister(rhs)};
2278 selector->Emit(kArmSmull, 2, outputs, 2, inputs);
2279
2280 // result operand needs shift operator.
2281 InstructionOperand shift_31 = g.UseImmediate(31);
2282 InstructionCode opcode =
2283 kArmCmp | AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_Operand2_R_ASR_I);
2284 selector->EmitWithContinuation(opcode, temp_operand, result_operand, shift_31,
2285 cont);
2286}
2287
2288} // namespace

2290template <typename Adapter>
2291void InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>::VisitInt32Mul(node_t node) {
2292 ArmOperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(this);
2293 if constexpr (Adapter::IsTurboshaft) {
2294 using namespace turboshaft; // NOLINT(build/namespaces)
2295 const WordBinopOp& mul = this->Get(node).template Cast<WordBinopOp>();
2296 int32_t constant_rhs;
2297 if (this->MatchIntegralWord32Constant(mul.right(), &constant_rhs) &&
2298 constant_rhs > 0) {
2299 if (base::bits::IsPowerOfTwo(constant_rhs - 1)) {
2300 Emit(kArmAdd | AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_Operand2_R_LSL_I),
2301 g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(mul.left()),
2302 g.UseRegister(mul.left()),
2303 g.TempImmediate(base::bits::WhichPowerOfTwo(constant_rhs - 1)));
2304 return;
2305 }
2306 if (constant_rhs < kMaxInt &&
2307 base::bits::IsPowerOfTwo(constant_rhs + 1)) {
2308 Emit(kArmRsb | AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_Operand2_R_LSL_I),
2309 g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(mul.left()),
2310 g.UseRegister(mul.left()),
2311 g.TempImmediate(base::bits::WhichPowerOfTwo(constant_rhs + 1)));
2312 return;
2313 }
2314 }
2315 VisitRRR(this, kArmMul, node);
2316 } else {
2317 Int32BinopMatcher m(node);
2318 if (m.right().HasResolvedValue() && m.right().ResolvedValue() > 0) {
2319 int32_t value = m.right().ResolvedValue();
2320 if (base::bits::IsPowerOfTwo(value - 1)) {
2321 Emit(kArmAdd | AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_Operand2_R_LSL_I),
2322 g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(m.left().node()),
2323 g.UseRegister(m.left().node()),
2324 g.TempImmediate(base::bits::WhichPowerOfTwo(value - 1)));
2325 return;
2326 }
2327 if (value < kMaxInt && base::bits::IsPowerOfTwo(value + 1)) {
2328 Emit(kArmRsb | AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_Operand2_R_LSL_I),
2329 g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(m.left().node()),
2330 g.UseRegister(m.left().node()),
2331 g.TempImmediate(base::bits::WhichPowerOfTwo(value + 1)));
2332 return;
2333 }
2334 }
2335 VisitRRR(this, kArmMul, node);
2336 }

2458template <typename Adapter>
2459void InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>::VisitFloat32Add(node_t node) {
2460 ArmOperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(this);
2461 if constexpr (Adapter::IsTurboshaft) {
2462 using namespace turboshaft; // NOLINT(build/namespaces)
2463 const FloatBinopOp& add = this->Get(node).template Cast<FloatBinopOp>();
2464 const Operation& lhs = this->Get(add.left());
2465 if (lhs.Is<Opmask::kFloat32Mul>() && CanCover(node, add.left())) {
2466 const FloatBinopOp& mul = lhs.Cast<FloatBinopOp>();
2467 Emit(kArmVmlaF32, g.DefineSameAsFirst(node), g.UseRegister(add.right()),
2468 g.UseRegister(mul.left()), g.UseRegister(mul.right()));
2469 return;
2470 }
2471 const Operation& rhs = this->Get(add.right());
2472 if (rhs.Is<Opmask::kFloat32Mul>() && CanCover(node, add.right())) {
2473 const FloatBinopOp& mul = rhs.Cast<FloatBinopOp>();
2474 Emit(kArmVmlaF32, g.DefineSameAsFirst(node), g.UseRegister(add.left()),
2475 g.UseRegister(mul.left()), g.UseRegister(mul.right()));
2476 return;
2477 }
2478 VisitRRR(this, kArmVaddF32, node);
2479 } else {
2480 Float32BinopMatcher m(node);
2481 if (m.left().IsFloat32Mul() && CanCover(node, m.left().node())) {
2482 Float32BinopMatcher mleft(m.left().node());
2483 Emit(kArmVmlaF32, g.DefineSameAsFirst(node),
2484 g.UseRegister(m.right().node()), g.UseRegister(mleft.left().node()),
2485 g.UseRegister(mleft.right().node()));
2486 return;
2487 }
2488 if (m.right().IsFloat32Mul() && CanCover(node, m.right().node())) {
2489 Float32BinopMatcher mright(m.right().node());
2490 Emit(kArmVmlaF32, g.DefineSameAsFirst(node),
2491 g.UseRegister(m.left().node()), g.UseRegister(mright.left().node()),
2492 g.UseRegister(mright.right().node()));
2493 return;
2494 }
2495 VisitRRR(this, kArmVaddF32, node);
2496 }

2630template <typename Adapter>
2631void InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>::EmitPrepareArguments(
2632 ZoneVector<PushParameter>* arguments, const CallDescriptor* call_descriptor,
2633 node_t node) {
2634 ArmOperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(this);
2635
2636 // Prepare for C function call.
2637 if (call_descriptor->IsCFunctionCall()) {
2638 Emit(kArchPrepareCallCFunction | MiscField::encode(static_cast<int>(
2639 call_descriptor->ParameterCount())),
2640 0, nullptr, 0, nullptr);
2641
2642 // Poke any stack arguments.
2643 for (size_t n = 0; n < arguments->size(); ++n) {
2644 PushParameter input = (*arguments)[n];
2645 if (this->valid(input.node)) {
2646 int slot = static_cast<int>(n);
2647 Emit(kArmPoke | MiscField::encode(slot), g.NoOutput(),
2648 g.UseRegister(input.node));
2649 }
2650 }
2651 } else {
2652 // Push any stack arguments.
2653 int stack_decrement = 0;
2654 for (PushParameter input : base::Reversed(*arguments)) {
2655 stack_decrement += kSystemPointerSize;
2656 // Skip any alignment holes in pushed nodes.
2657 if (!this->valid(input.node)) continue;
2658 InstructionOperand decrement = g.UseImmediate(stack_decrement);
2659 stack_decrement = 0;
2660 Emit(kArmPush, g.NoOutput(), decrement, g.UseRegister(input.node));
2661 }
2662 }
2663}
2664
2665template <typename Adapter>
2666void InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>::EmitPrepareResults(
2667 ZoneVector<PushParameter>* results, const CallDescriptor* call_descriptor,
2668 node_t node) {
2669 ArmOperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(this);
2670
2671 for (PushParameter output : *results) {
2672 if (!output.location.IsCallerFrameSlot()) continue;
2673 // Skip any alignment holes in nodes.
2674 if (this->valid(output.node)) {
2675 DCHECK(!call_descriptor->IsCFunctionCall());
2676 if (output.location.GetType() == MachineType::Float32()) {
2677 MarkAsFloat32(output.node);
2678 } else if (output.location.GetType() == MachineType::Float64()) {
2679 MarkAsFloat64(output.node);
2680 } else if (output.location.GetType() == MachineType::Simd128()) {
2681 MarkAsSimd128(output.node);
2682 }
2683 int offset = call_descriptor->GetOffsetToReturns();
2684 int reverse_slot = -output.location.GetLocation() - offset;
2685 Emit(kArmPeek, g.DefineAsRegister(output.node),
2686 g.UseImmediate(reverse_slot));
2687 }
2688 }
2689}

2698// Shared routine for multiple compare operations.
2699template <typename Adapter>
2700void VisitCompare(InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>* selector,
2701 InstructionCode opcode, InstructionOperand left,
2702 InstructionOperand right, FlagsContinuationT<Adapter>* cont) {
2703 selector->EmitWithContinuation(opcode, left, right, cont);
2704}
2705
2706// Shared routine for multiple float32 compare operations.
2707template <typename Adapter>
2708void VisitFloat32Compare(InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>* selector,
2709 typename Adapter::node_t node,
2710 FlagsContinuationT<Adapter>* cont) {
2711 ArmOperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(selector);
2712 if constexpr (Adapter::IsTurboshaft) {
2713 using namespace turboshaft; // NOLINT(build/namespaces)
2714 const ComparisonOp& cmp = selector->Get(node).template Cast<ComparisonOp>();
2715 if (selector->MatchZero(cmp.right())) {
2716 VisitCompare(selector, kArmVcmpF32, g.UseRegister(cmp.left()),
2717 g.UseImmediate(cmp.right()), cont);
2718 } else if (selector->MatchZero(cmp.left())) {
2719 cont->Commute();
2720 VisitCompare(selector, kArmVcmpF32, g.UseRegister(cmp.right()),
2721 g.UseImmediate(cmp.left()), cont);
2722 } else {
2723 VisitCompare(selector, kArmVcmpF32, g.UseRegister(cmp.left()),
2724 g.UseRegister(cmp.right()), cont);
2725 }
2726 } else {
2727 Float32BinopMatcher m(node);
2728 if (m.right().Is(0.0f)) {
2729 VisitCompare(selector, kArmVcmpF32, g.UseRegister(m.left().node()),
2730 g.UseImmediate(m.right().node()), cont);
2731 } else if (m.left().Is(0.0f)) {
2732 cont->Commute();
2733 VisitCompare(selector, kArmVcmpF32, g.UseRegister(m.right().node()),
2734 g.UseImmediate(m.left().node()), cont);
2735 } else {
2736 VisitCompare(selector, kArmVcmpF32, g.UseRegister(m.left().node()),
2737 g.UseRegister(m.right().node()), cont);
2738 }
2739 }
2740}

2742// Shared routine for multiple float64 compare operations.
2743template <typename Adapter>
2744void VisitFloat64Compare(InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>* selector,
2745 typename Adapter::node_t node,
2746 FlagsContinuationT<Adapter>* cont) {
2747 ArmOperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(selector);
2748 if constexpr (Adapter::IsTurboshaft) {
2749 using namespace turboshaft; // NOLINT(build/namespaces)
2750 const ComparisonOp& op = selector->Get(node).template Cast<ComparisonOp>();
2751 if (selector->MatchZero(op.right())) {
2752 VisitCompare(selector, kArmVcmpF64, g.UseRegister(op.left()),
2753 g.UseImmediate(op.right()), cont);
2754 } else if (selector->MatchZero(op.left())) {
2755 cont->Commute();
2756 VisitCompare(selector, kArmVcmpF64, g.UseRegister(op.right()),
2757 g.UseImmediate(op.left()), cont);
2758 } else {
2759 VisitCompare(selector, kArmVcmpF64, g.UseRegister(op.left()),
2760 g.UseRegister(op.right()), cont);
2761 }
2762 } else {
2763 Float64BinopMatcher m(node);
2764 if (m.right().Is(0.0)) {
2765 VisitCompare(selector, kArmVcmpF64, g.UseRegister(m.left().node()),
2766 g.UseImmediate(m.right().node()), cont);
2767 } else if (m.left().Is(0.0)) {
2768 cont->Commute();
2769 VisitCompare(selector, kArmVcmpF64, g.UseRegister(m.right().node()),
2770 g.UseImmediate(m.left().node()), cont);
2771 } else {
2772 VisitCompare(selector, kArmVcmpF64, g.UseRegister(m.left().node()),
2773 g.UseRegister(m.right().node()), cont);
2774 }
2775 }
