2778// Check whether we can convert:
2779// ((a <op> b) cmp 0), b.<cond>
2780// to:
2781// (a <ops> b), b.<cond'>
2782// where <ops> is the flag setting version of <op>.
2783// We only generate conditions <cond'> that are a combination of the N
2784// and Z flags. This avoids the need to make this function dependent on
2785// the flag-setting operation.
2786bool CanUseFlagSettingBinop(FlagsCondition cond) {
2787 switch (cond) {
2788 case kEqual:
2789 case kNotEqual:
2790 case kSignedLessThan:
2791 case kSignedGreaterThanOrEqual:
2792 case kUnsignedLessThanOrEqual: // x <= 0 -> x == 0
2793 case kUnsignedGreaterThan: // x > 0 -> x != 0
2794 return true;
2795 default:
2796 return false;
2797 }
2798}
2799
2800// Map <cond> to <cond'> so that the following transformation is possible:
2801// ((a <op> b) cmp 0), b.<cond>
2802// to:
2803// (a <ops> b), b.<cond'>
2804// where <ops> is the flag setting version of <op>.
2805FlagsCondition MapForFlagSettingBinop(FlagsCondition cond) {
2806 DCHECK(CanUseFlagSettingBinop(cond));
2807 switch (cond) {
2808 case kEqual:
2809 case kNotEqual:
2810 return cond;
2811 case kSignedLessThan:
2812 return kNegative;
2813 case kSignedGreaterThanOrEqual:
2814 return kPositiveOrZero;
2815 case kUnsignedLessThanOrEqual: // x <= 0 -> x == 0
2816 return kEqual;
2817 case kUnsignedGreaterThan: // x > 0 -> x != 0
2818 return kNotEqual;
2819 default:
2820 UNREACHABLE();
2821 }
2822}
2823
2824// Check if we can perform the transformation:
2825// ((a <op> b) cmp 0), b.<cond>
2826// to:
2827// (a <ops> b), b.<cond'>
2828// where <ops> is the flag setting version of <op>, and if so,
2829// updates {node}, {opcode} and {cont} accordingly.
2830template <typename Adapter>
2831void MaybeReplaceCmpZeroWithFlagSettingBinop(
2832 InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>* selector, typename Adapter::node_t* node,
2833 typename Adapter::node_t binop, InstructionCode* opcode,
2834 FlagsCondition cond, FlagsContinuationT<Adapter>* cont) {
2835 InstructionCode binop_opcode;
2836 InstructionCode no_output_opcode;
2837 if constexpr (Adapter::IsTurboshaft) {
2838 using namespace turboshaft; // NOLINT(build/namespaces)
2839 const Operation& op = selector->Get(binop);
2840 if (op.Is<Opmask::kWord32Add>()) {
2841 binop_opcode = kArmAdd;
2842 no_output_opcode = kArmCmn;
2843 } else if (op.Is<Opmask::kWord32BitwiseAnd>()) {
2844 binop_opcode = kArmAnd;
2845 no_output_opcode = kArmTst;
2846 } else if (op.Is<Opmask::kWord32BitwiseOr>()) {
2847 binop_opcode = kArmOrr;
2848 no_output_opcode = kArmOrr;
2849 } else if (op.Is<Opmask::kWord32BitwiseXor>()) {
2850 binop_opcode = kArmEor;
2851 no_output_opcode = kArmTeq;
2852 }
2853 } else {
2854 switch (binop->opcode()) {
2855 case IrOpcode::kInt32Add:
2856 binop_opcode = kArmAdd;
2857 no_output_opcode = kArmCmn;
2858 break;
2859 case IrOpcode::kWord32And:
2860 binop_opcode = kArmAnd;
2861 no_output_opcode = kArmTst;
2862 break;
2863 case IrOpcode::kWord32Or:
2864 binop_opcode = kArmOrr;
2865 no_output_opcode = kArmOrr;
2866 break;
2867 case IrOpcode::kWord32Xor:
2868 binop_opcode = kArmEor;
2869 no_output_opcode = kArmTeq;
2870 break;
2871 default:
2872 UNREACHABLE();
2873 }
2874 }
2875
2876 if (selector->CanCover(*node, binop)) {
2877 // The comparison is the only user of {node}.
2878 cont->Overwrite(MapForFlagSettingBinop(cond));
2879 *opcode = no_output_opcode;
2880 *node = binop;
2881 } else if (selector->IsOnlyUserOfNodeInSameBlock(*node, binop)) {
2882 // We can also handle the case where the {node} and the comparison are in
2883 // the same basic block, and the comparison is the only user of {node} in
2884 // this basic block ({node} has users in other basic blocks).
2885 cont->Overwrite(MapForFlagSettingBinop(cond));
2886 *opcode = binop_opcode;
2887 *node = binop;
2888 }
2889}
2890
2891// Shared routine for multiple word compare operations.
2892template <typename Adapter>
2893void VisitWordCompare(InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>* selector,
2894 typename Adapter::node_t node, InstructionCode opcode,
2895 FlagsContinuationT<Adapter>* cont) {
2896 ArmOperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(selector);
2897 typename Adapter::node_t lhs = selector->input_at(node, 0);
2898 typename Adapter::node_t rhs = selector->input_at(node, 1);
2899 InstructionOperand inputs[3];
2900 size_t input_count = 0;
2901 InstructionOperand outputs[2];
2902 size_t output_count = 0;
2903 bool has_result = (opcode != kArmCmp) && (opcode != kArmCmn) &&
2904 (opcode != kArmTst) && (opcode != kArmTeq);
2905
2906 if (TryMatchImmediateOrShift(selector, &opcode, rhs, &input_count,
2907 &inputs[1])) {
2908 inputs[0] = g.UseRegister(lhs);
2909 input_count++;
2910 } else if (TryMatchImmediateOrShift(selector, &opcode, lhs, &input_count,
2911 &inputs[1])) {
2912 if constexpr (Adapter::IsTurboshaft) {
2913 using namespace turboshaft; // NOLINT(build/namespaces)
2914 const Operation& op = selector->Get(node);
2915 if (const ComparisonOp* cmp = op.TryCast<ComparisonOp>()) {
2916 if (!ComparisonOp::IsCommutative(cmp->kind)) cont->Commute();
2917 } else if (const WordBinopOp* binop = op.TryCast<WordBinopOp>()) {
2918 if (!WordBinopOp::IsCommutative(binop->kind)) cont->Commute();
2919 } else {
2920 UNREACHABLE();
2921 }
2922 } else {
2923 if (!node->op()->HasProperty(Operator::kCommutative)) cont->Commute();
2924 }
2925 inputs[0] = g.UseRegister(rhs);
2926 input_count++;
2927 } else {
2928 opcode |= AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_Operand2_R);
2929 inputs[input_count++] = g.UseRegister(lhs);
2930 inputs[input_count++] = g.UseRegister(rhs);
2931 }
2932
2933 if (has_result) {
2934 if (cont->IsDeoptimize()) {
2935 // If we can deoptimize as a result of the binop, we need to make sure
2936 // that the deopt inputs are not overwritten by the binop result. One
2937 // way to achieve that is to declare the output register as
2938 // same-as-first.
2939 outputs[output_count++] = g.DefineSameAsFirst(node);
2940 } else {
2941 outputs[output_count++] = g.DefineAsRegister(node);
2942 }
2943 }
2944
2945 DCHECK_NE(0u, input_count);
2946 DCHECK_GE(arraysize(inputs), input_count);
2947 DCHECK_GE(arraysize(outputs), output_count);
2948
2949 selector->EmitWithContinuation(opcode, output_count, outputs, input_count,
2950 inputs, cont);
2951}
2952
2953template <typename Adapter>
2954void VisitWordCompare(InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>* selector,
2955 typename Adapter::node_t node,
2956 FlagsContinuationT<Adapter>* cont) {
2957 if constexpr (Adapter::IsTurboshaft) {
2958 using namespace turboshaft; // NOLINT(build/namespaces)
2959 InstructionCode opcode = kArmCmp;
2960 const ComparisonOp& comparison =
2961 selector->Get(node).template Cast<ComparisonOp>();
2962 const Operation& lhs = selector->Get(comparison.left());
2963 const Operation& rhs = selector->Get(comparison.right());
2964
2965 FlagsCondition cond = cont->condition();
2966 if (selector->MatchIntegralZero(comparison.right()) &&
2967 (lhs.Is<Opmask::kWord32Add>() || lhs.Is<Opmask::kWord32BitwiseOr>() ||
2968 lhs.Is<Opmask::kWord32BitwiseAnd>() ||
2969 lhs.Is<Opmask::kWord32BitwiseXor>())) {
2970 // Emit flag setting instructions for comparisons against zero.
2971 if (CanUseFlagSettingBinop(cond)) {
2972 MaybeReplaceCmpZeroWithFlagSettingBinop(
2973 selector, &node, comparison.left(), &opcode, cond, cont);
2974 }
2975 } else if (selector->MatchIntegralZero(comparison.left()) &&
2976 (rhs.Is<Opmask::kWord32Add>() ||
2977 rhs.Is<Opmask::kWord32BitwiseOr>() ||
2978 rhs.Is<Opmask::kWord32BitwiseAnd>() ||
2979 rhs.Is<Opmask::kWord32BitwiseXor>())) {
2980 // Same as above, but we need to commute the condition before we
2981 // continue with the rest of the checks.
2982 cond = CommuteFlagsCondition(cond);
2983 if (CanUseFlagSettingBinop(cond)) {
2984 MaybeReplaceCmpZeroWithFlagSettingBinop(
2985 selector, &node, comparison.right(), &opcode, cond, cont);
2986 }
2987 }
2988
2989 VisitWordCompare(selector, node, opcode, cont);
2990 } else {
2991 InstructionCode opcode = kArmCmp;
2992 Int32BinopMatcher m(node);
2993
2994 FlagsCondition cond = cont->condition();
2995 if (m.right().Is(0) && (m.left().IsInt32Add() || m.left().IsWord32Or() ||
2996 m.left().IsWord32And() || m.left().IsWord32Xor())) {
2997 // Emit flag setting instructions for comparisons against zero.
2998 if (CanUseFlagSettingBinop(cond)) {
2999 Node* binop = m.left().node();
3000 MaybeReplaceCmpZeroWithFlagSettingBinop(selector, &node, binop, &opcode,
3001 cond, cont);
3002 }
3003 } else if (m.left().Is(0) &&
3004 (m.right().IsInt32Add() || m.right().IsWord32Or() ||
3005 m.right().IsWord32And() || m.right().IsWord32Xor())) {
3006 // Same as above, but we need to commute the condition before we
3007 // continue with the rest of the checks.
3008 cond = CommuteFlagsCondition(cond);
3009 if (CanUseFlagSettingBinop(cond)) {
3010 Node* binop = m.right().node();
3011 MaybeReplaceCmpZeroWithFlagSettingBinop(selector, &node, binop, &opcode,
3012 cond, cont);
3013 }
3014 }
3015
3016 VisitWordCompare(selector, node, opcode, cont);
3017 }
3018}

3022// Shared routine for word comparisons against zero.
3023template <typename Adapter>
3024void InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>::VisitWordCompareZero(
3025 node_t user, node_t value, FlagsContinuation* cont) {
3026 // Try to combine with comparisons against 0 by simply inverting the branch.
3027 while (value->opcode() == IrOpcode::kWord32Equal && CanCover(user, value)) {
3028 Int32BinopMatcher m(value);
3029 if (!m.right().Is(0)) break;
3030
3031 user = value;
3032 value = m.left().node();
3033 cont->Negate();
3034 }
3035
3036 if (CanCover(user, value)) {
3037 switch (value->opcode()) {
3038 case IrOpcode::kWord32Equal:
3039 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kEqual);
3040 return VisitWordCompare(this, value, cont);
3041 case IrOpcode::kInt32LessThan:
3042 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kSignedLessThan);
3043 return VisitWordCompare(this, value, cont);
3044 case IrOpcode::kInt32LessThanOrEqual:
3045 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kSignedLessThanOrEqual);
3046 return VisitWordCompare(this, value, cont);
3047 case IrOpcode::kUint32LessThan:
3048 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kUnsignedLessThan);
3049 return VisitWordCompare(this, value, cont);
3050 case IrOpcode::kUint32LessThanOrEqual:
3051 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kUnsignedLessThanOrEqual);
3052 return VisitWordCompare(this, value, cont);
3053 case IrOpcode::kFloat32Equal:
3054 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kEqual);
3055 return VisitFloat32Compare(this, value, cont);
3056 case IrOpcode::kFloat32LessThan:
3057 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kFloatLessThan);
3058 return VisitFloat32Compare(this, value, cont);
3059 case IrOpcode::kFloat32LessThanOrEqual:
3060 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kFloatLessThanOrEqual);
3061 return VisitFloat32Compare(this, value, cont);
3062 case IrOpcode::kFloat64Equal:
3063 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kEqual);
3064 return VisitFloat64Compare(this, value, cont);
3065 case IrOpcode::kFloat64LessThan:
3066 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kFloatLessThan);
3067 return VisitFloat64Compare(this, value, cont);
3068 case IrOpcode::kFloat64LessThanOrEqual:
3069 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kFloatLessThanOrEqual);
3070 return VisitFloat64Compare(this, value, cont);
3071 case IrOpcode::kProjection:
3072 // Check if this is the overflow output projection of an
3073 // <Operation>WithOverflow node.
3074 if (ProjectionIndexOf(value->op()) == 1u) {
3075 // We cannot combine the <Operation>WithOverflow with this branch
3076 // unless the 0th projection (the use of the actual value of the
3077 // <Operation> is either nullptr, which means there's no use of the
3078 // actual value, or was already defined, which means it is scheduled
3079 // *AFTER* this branch).
3080 Node* const node = value->InputAt(0);
3081 Node* const result = NodeProperties::FindProjection(node, 0);
3082 if (!result || IsDefined(result)) {
3083 switch (node->opcode()) {
3084 case IrOpcode::kInt32AddWithOverflow:
3085 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kOverflow);
3086 return VisitBinop(this, node, kArmAdd, kArmAdd, cont);
3087 case IrOpcode::kInt32SubWithOverflow:
3088 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kOverflow);
3089 return VisitBinop(this, node, kArmSub, kArmRsb, cont);
3090 case IrOpcode::kInt32MulWithOverflow:
3091 // ARM doesn't set the overflow flag for multiplication, so we
3092 // need to test on kNotEqual. Here is the code sequence used:
3093 // smull resultlow, resulthigh, left, right
3094 // cmp resulthigh, Operand(resultlow, ASR, 31)
3095 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kNotEqual);
3096 return EmitInt32MulWithOverflow(this, node, cont);
3097 default:
3098 break;
3099 }
3100 }
3101 }
3102 break;
3103 case IrOpcode::kInt32Add:
3104 return VisitWordCompare(this, value, kArmCmn, cont);
3105 case IrOpcode::kInt32Sub:
3106 return VisitWordCompare(this, value, kArmCmp, cont);
3107 case IrOpcode::kWord32And:
3108 return VisitWordCompare(this, value, kArmTst, cont);
3109 case IrOpcode::kWord32Or:
3110 return VisitBinop(this, value, kArmOrr, kArmOrr, cont);
3111 case IrOpcode::kWord32Xor:
3112 return VisitWordCompare(this, value, kArmTeq, cont);
3113 case IrOpcode::kWord32Sar:
3114 return VisitShift(this, value, TryMatchASR<Adapter>, cont);
3115 case IrOpcode::kWord32Shl:
3116 return VisitShift(this, value, TryMatchLSL<Adapter>, cont);
3117 case IrOpcode::kWord32Shr:
3118 return VisitShift(this, value, TryMatchLSR<Adapter>, cont);
3119 case IrOpcode::kWord32Ror:
3120 return VisitShift(this, value, TryMatchROR<Adapter>, cont);
3121 case IrOpcode::kStackPointerGreaterThan:
3122 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kStackPointerGreaterThanCondition);
3123 return VisitStackPointerGreaterThan(value, cont);
3124 default:
3125 break;
3126 }
3127 }
3128
3129 if (user->opcode() == IrOpcode::kWord32Equal) {
3130 return VisitWordCompare(this, user, cont);
3131 }
3132
3133 // Continuation could not be combined with a compare, emit compare against
3134 // 0.
3135 ArmOperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(this);
3136 InstructionCode const opcode =
3137 kArmTst | AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_Operand2_R);
3138 InstructionOperand const value_operand = g.UseRegister(value);
3139 EmitWithContinuation(opcode, value_operand, value_operand, cont);
3140}

3142template <>
3143void InstructionSelectorT<TurboshaftAdapter>::VisitWordCompareZero(
3144 node_t user, node_t value, FlagsContinuation* cont) {
3145 using namespace turboshaft; // NOLINT(build/namespaces)
3146 // Try to combine with comparisons against 0 by simply inverting the branch.
3147 ConsumeEqualZero(&user, &value, cont);
3148
3149 if (CanCover(user, value)) {
3150 const Operation& value_op = Get(value);
3151 if (const ComparisonOp* comparison = value_op.TryCast<ComparisonOp>()) {
3152 switch (comparison->rep.MapTaggedToWord().value()) {
3153 case RegisterRepresentation::Word32():
3154 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(
3155 GetComparisonFlagCondition(*comparison));
3156 return VisitWordCompare(this, value, cont);
3157 case RegisterRepresentation::Float32():
3158 switch (comparison->kind) {
3159 case ComparisonOp::Kind::kEqual:
3160 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kEqual);
3161 return VisitFloat32Compare(this, value, cont);
3162 case ComparisonOp::Kind::kSignedLessThan:
3163 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kFloatLessThan);
3164 return VisitFloat32Compare(this, value, cont);
3165 case ComparisonOp::Kind::kSignedLessThanOrEqual:
3166 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kFloatLessThanOrEqual);
3167 return VisitFloat32Compare(this, value, cont);
3168 default:
3169 UNREACHABLE();
3170 }
3171 case RegisterRepresentation::Float64():
3172 switch (comparison->kind) {
3173 case ComparisonOp::Kind::kEqual:
3174 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kEqual);
3175 return VisitFloat64Compare(this, value, cont);
3176 case ComparisonOp::Kind::kSignedLessThan:
3177 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kFloatLessThan);
3178 return VisitFloat64Compare(this, value, cont);
3179 case ComparisonOp::Kind::kSignedLessThanOrEqual:
3180 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kFloatLessThanOrEqual);
3181 return VisitFloat64Compare(this, value, cont);
3182 default:
3183 UNREACHABLE();
3184 }
3185 default:
3186 break;
3187 }
3188 } else if (const ProjectionOp* projection =
3189 value_op.TryCast<ProjectionOp>()) {
3190 // Check if this is the overflow output projection of an
3191 // <Operation>WithOverflow node.
3192 if (projection->index == 1u) {
3193 // We cannot combine the <Operation>WithOverflow with this branch
3194 // unless the 0th projection (the use of the actual value of the
3195 // <Operation> is either nullptr, which means there's no use of the
3196 // actual value, or was already defined, which means it is scheduled
3197 // *AFTER* this branch).
3198 OpIndex node = projection->input();
3199 OpIndex result = FindProjection(node, 0);
3200 if (!result.valid() || IsDefined(result)) {
3201 if (const OverflowCheckedBinopOp* binop =
3202 TryCast<OverflowCheckedBinopOp>(node)) {
3203 DCHECK_EQ(binop->rep, WordRepresentation::Word32());
3204 switch (binop->kind) {
3205 case OverflowCheckedBinopOp::Kind::kSignedAdd:
3206 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kOverflow);
3207 return VisitBinop(this, node, kArmAdd, kArmAdd, cont);
3208 case OverflowCheckedBinopOp::Kind::kSignedSub:
3209 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kOverflow);
3210 return VisitBinop(this, node, kArmSub, kArmRsb, cont);
3211 case OverflowCheckedBinopOp::Kind::kSignedMul:
3212 // ARM doesn't set the overflow flag for multiplication, so we
3213 // need to test on kNotEqual. Here is the code sequence used:
3214 // smull resultlow, resulthigh, left, right
3215 // cmp resulthigh, Operand(resultlow, ASR, 31)
3216 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kNotEqual);
3217 return EmitInt32MulWithOverflow(this, node, cont);
3218 }
3219 }
3220 }
3221 }
3222 } else if (value_op.Is<Opmask::kWord32Add>()) {
3223 return VisitWordCompare(this, value, kArmCmn, cont);
3224 } else if (value_op.Is<Opmask::kWord32Sub>()) {
3225 return VisitWordCompare(this, value, kArmCmp, cont);
3226 } else if (value_op.Is<Opmask::kWord32BitwiseAnd>()) {
3227 return VisitWordCompare(this, value, kArmTst, cont);
3228 } else if (value_op.Is<Opmask::kWord32BitwiseOr>()) {
3229 return VisitBinop(this, value, kArmOrr, kArmOrr, cont);
3230 } else if (value_op.Is<Opmask::kWord32BitwiseXor>()) {
3231 return VisitWordCompare(this, value, kArmTeq, cont);
3232 } else if (value_op.Is<Opmask::kWord32ShiftRightArithmetic>()) {
3233 return VisitShift(this, value, TryMatchASR<TurboshaftAdapter>, cont);
3234 } else if (value_op.Is<Opmask::kWord32ShiftLeft>()) {
3235 return VisitShift(this, value, TryMatchLSL<TurboshaftAdapter>, cont);
3236 } else if (value_op.Is<Opmask::kWord32ShiftRightLogical>()) {
3237 return VisitShift(this, value, TryMatchLSR<TurboshaftAdapter>, cont);
3238 } else if (value_op.Is<Opmask::kWord32RotateRight>()) {
3239 return VisitShift(this, value, TryMatchROR<TurboshaftAdapter>, cont);
3240 } else if (value_op.Is<StackPointerGreaterThanOp>()) {
3241 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kStackPointerGreaterThanCondition);
3242 return VisitStackPointerGreaterThan(value, cont);
3243 }
3244 }
3245
3246 if (Get(user).Is<Opmask::kWord32Equal>()) {
3247 return VisitWordCompare(this, user, cont);
3248 }
3249
3250 // Continuation could not be combined with a compare, emit compare against
3251 // 0.
3252 ArmOperandGeneratorT<TurboshaftAdapter> g(this);
3253 InstructionCode const opcode =
3254 kArmTst | AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_Operand2_R);
3255 InstructionOperand const value_operand = g.UseRegister(value);
3256 EmitWithContinuation(opcode, value_operand, value_operand, cont);
3257}

3259template <typename Adapter>
3260void InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>::VisitSwitch(node_t node,
3261 const SwitchInfo& sw) {
3262 ArmOperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(this);
3263 InstructionOperand value_operand = g.UseRegister(this->input_at(node, 0));
3264
3265 // Emit either ArchTableSwitch or ArchBinarySearchSwitch.
3266 if (enable_switch_jump_table_ ==
3267 InstructionSelector::kEnableSwitchJumpTable) {
3268 static const size_t kMaxTableSwitchValueRange = 2 << 16;
3269 size_t table_space_cost = 4 + sw.value_range();
3270 size_t table_time_cost = 3;
3271 size_t lookup_space_cost = 3 + 2 * sw.case_count();
3272 size_t lookup_time_cost = sw.case_count();
3273 if (sw.case_count() > 0 &&
3274 table_space_cost + 3 * table_time_cost <=
3275 lookup_space_cost + 3 * lookup_time_cost &&
3276 sw.min_value() > std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min() &&
3277 sw.value_range() <= kMaxTableSwitchValueRange) {
3278 InstructionOperand index_operand = value_operand;
3279 if (sw.min_value()) {
3280 index_operand = g.TempRegister();
3281 Emit(kArmSub | AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_Operand2_I),
3282 index_operand, value_operand, g.TempImmediate(sw.min_value()));
3283 }
3284 // Generate a table lookup.
3285 return EmitTableSwitch(sw, index_operand);
3286 }
3287 }
3288
3289 // Generate a tree of conditional jumps.
3290 return EmitBinarySearchSwitch(sw, value_operand);
3291}

3348template <typename Adapter>
3349void InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>::VisitInt32SubWithOverflow(node_t node) {
3350 node_t ovf = FindProjection(node, 1);
3351 if (this->valid(ovf)) {
3352 FlagsContinuation cont = FlagsContinuation::ForSet(kOverflow, ovf);
3353 return VisitBinop(this, node, kArmSub, kArmRsb, &cont);
3354 }
3355 FlagsContinuation cont;
3356 VisitBinop(this, node, kArmSub, kArmRsb, &cont);
3357}
3358
3359template <typename Adapter>
3360void InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>::VisitInt32MulWithOverflow(node_t node) {
3361 node_t ovf = FindProjection(node, 1);
3362 if (this->valid(ovf)) {
3363 // ARM doesn't set the overflow flag for multiplication, so we need to
3364 // test on kNotEqual. Here is the code sequence used:
3365 // smull resultlow, resulthigh, left, right
3366 // cmp resulthigh, Operand(resultlow, ASR, 31)
3367 FlagsContinuation cont = FlagsContinuation::ForSet(kNotEqual, ovf);
3368 return EmitInt32MulWithOverflow(this, node, &cont);
3369 }
3370 FlagsContinuation cont;
3371 EmitInt32MulWithOverflow(this, node, &cont);
3372}

3412template <typename Adapter>
3413void InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>::VisitFloat64InsertLowWord32(node_t node) {
3414 if constexpr (Adapter::IsTurboshaft) {
3415 UNIMPLEMENTED();
3416 } else {
3417 ArmOperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(this);
3418 Node* left = node->InputAt(0);
3419 Node* right = node->InputAt(1);
3420 if (left->opcode() == IrOpcode::kFloat64InsertHighWord32 &&
3421 CanCover(node, left)) {
3422 left = left->InputAt(1);
3423 Emit(kArmVmovF64U32U32, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(right),
3424 g.UseRegister(left));
3425 return;
3426 }
3427 Emit(kArmVmovLowF64U32, g.DefineSameAsFirst(node), g.UseRegister(left),
3428 g.UseRegister(right));
3429 }
3430}

3477template <typename Adapter>
3478void InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>::VisitWord32AtomicLoad(node_t node) {
3479 // The memory order is ignored as both acquire and sequentially consistent
3480 // loads can emit LDR; DMB ISH.
3481 // https://www.cl.cam.ac.uk/~pes20/cpp/cpp0xmappings.html
3482 ArmOperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(this);
3483 auto load = this->load_view(node);
3484 node_t base = load.base();
3485 node_t index = load.index();
3486 ArchOpcode opcode;
3487 LoadRepresentation load_rep = load.loaded_rep();
3488 switch (load_rep.representation()) {
3489 case MachineRepresentation::kWord8:
3490 opcode = load_rep.IsSigned() ? kAtomicLoadInt8 : kAtomicLoadUint8;
3491 break;
3492 case MachineRepresentation::kWord16:
3493 opcode = load_rep.IsSigned() ? kAtomicLoadInt16 : kAtomicLoadUint16;
3494 break;
3495 case MachineRepresentation::kTaggedSigned: // Fall through.
3496 case MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer: // Fall through.
3497 case MachineRepresentation::kTagged: // Fall through.
3498 case MachineRepresentation::kWord32:
3499 opcode = kAtomicLoadWord32;
3500 break;
3501 default:
3502 UNREACHABLE();
3503 }
3504 Emit(opcode | AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_Offset_RR),
3505 g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(base), g.UseRegister(index));
3506}

3519template <typename Adapter>
3520void InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>::VisitWord32AtomicExchange(node_t node) {
3521 ArmOperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(this);
3522 auto atomic_op = this->atomic_rmw_view(node);
3523 ArchOpcode opcode;
3524 if constexpr (Adapter::IsTurboshaft) {
3525 using namespace turboshaft; // NOLINT(build/namespaces)
3526 const AtomicRMWOp& atomic_op = this->Get(node).template Cast<AtomicRMWOp>();
3527 if (atomic_op.memory_rep == MemoryRepresentation::Int8()) {
3528 opcode = kAtomicExchangeInt8;
3529 } else if (atomic_op.memory_rep == MemoryRepresentation::Uint8()) {
3530 opcode = kAtomicExchangeUint8;
3531 } else if (atomic_op.memory_rep == MemoryRepresentation::Int16()) {
3532 opcode = kAtomicExchangeInt16;
3533 } else if (atomic_op.memory_rep == MemoryRepresentation::Uint16()) {
3534 opcode = kAtomicExchangeUint16;
3535 } else if (atomic_op.memory_rep == MemoryRepresentation::Int32() ||
3536 atomic_op.memory_rep == MemoryRepresentation::Uint32()) {
3537 opcode = kAtomicExchangeWord32;
3538 } else {
3539 UNREACHABLE();
3540 }
3541 } else {
3542 MachineType type = AtomicOpType(node->op());
3543 if (type == MachineType::Int8()) {
3544 opcode = kAtomicExchangeInt8;
3545 } else if (type == MachineType::Uint8()) {
3546 opcode = kAtomicExchangeUint8;
3547 } else if (type == MachineType::Int16()) {
3548 opcode = kAtomicExchangeInt16;
3549 } else if (type == MachineType::Uint16()) {
3550 opcode = kAtomicExchangeUint16;
3551 } else if (type == MachineType::Int32() || type == MachineType::Uint32()) {
3552 opcode = kAtomicExchangeWord32;
3553 } else {
3554 UNREACHABLE();
3555 }
3556 }
3557
3558 AddressingMode addressing_mode = kMode_Offset_RR;
3559 InstructionOperand inputs[3];
3560 size_t input_count = 0;
3561 inputs[input_count++] = g.UseRegister(atomic_op.base());
3562 inputs[input_count++] = g.UseRegister(atomic_op.index());
3563 inputs[input_count++] = g.UseUniqueRegister(atomic_op.value());
3564 InstructionOperand outputs[1];
3565 outputs[0] = g.DefineAsRegister(node);
3566 InstructionOperand temps[] = {g.TempRegister(), g.TempRegister()};
3567 InstructionCode code = opcode | AddressingModeField::encode(addressing_mode);
3568 Emit(code, 1, outputs, input_count, inputs, arraysize(temps), temps);
3569}

3589 opcode = kAtomicCompareExchangeInt16;
3590 } else if (atomic_op.memory_rep == MemoryRepresentation::Uint16()) {
3591 opcode = kAtomicCompareExchangeUint16;

3593 atomic_op.memory_rep == MemoryRepresentation::Uint32()) {
3594 opcode = kAtomicCompareExchangeWord32;

3699template <typename Adapter>
3700void InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>::VisitWord32AtomicPairLoad(node_t node) {
3701 ArmOperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(this);
3702 node_t base = this->input_at(node, 0);
3703 node_t index = this->input_at(node, 1);
3704 InstructionOperand inputs[3];
3705 size_t input_count = 0;
3706 inputs[input_count++] = g.UseUniqueRegister(base);
3707 inputs[input_count++] = g.UseUniqueRegister(index);
3708 InstructionOperand temps[1];
3709 size_t temp_count = 0;
3710 InstructionOperand outputs[2];
3711 size_t output_count = 0;
3712
3713 node_t projection0 = FindProjection(node, 0);
3714 node_t projection1 = FindProjection(node, 1);
3715 if (this->valid(projection0) && this->valid(projection1)) {
3716 outputs[output_count++] = g.DefineAsFixed(projection0, r0);
3717 outputs[output_count++] = g.DefineAsFixed(projection1, r1);
3718 temps[temp_count++] = g.TempRegister();
3719 } else if (this->valid(projection0)) {
3720 inputs[input_count++] = g.UseImmediate(0);
3721 outputs[output_count++] = g.DefineAsRegister(projection0);
3722 } else if (this->valid(projection1)) {
3723 inputs[input_count++] = g.UseImmediate(4);
3724 temps[temp_count++] = g.TempRegister();
3725 outputs[output_count++] = g.DefineAsRegister(projection1);
3726 } else {
3727 // There is no use of the loaded value, we don't need to generate code.
3728 return;
3729 }
3730 Emit(kArmWord32AtomicPairLoad, output_count, outputs, input_count, inputs,
3731 temp_count, temps);
3732}

3835 temps[temp_count++] = g.TempRegister();

4015template <typename Adapter>
4016void InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>::VisitS128Const(node_t node) {
4017 ArmOperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(this);
4018 uint32_t val[kSimd128Size / sizeof(uint32_t)];
4019 if constexpr (Adapter::IsTurboshaft) {
4020 const turboshaft::Simd128ConstantOp& constant =
4021 this->Get(node).template Cast<turboshaft::Simd128ConstantOp>();
4022 memcpy(val, constant.value, kSimd128Size);
4023 } else {
4024 memcpy(val, S128ImmediateParameterOf(node->op()).data(), kSimd128Size);
4025 }
4026 // If all bytes are zeros, avoid emitting code for generic constants.
4027 bool all_zeros = !(val[0] || val[1] || val[2] || val[3]);
4028 bool all_ones = val[0] == UINT32_MAX && val[1] == UINT32_MAX &&
4029 val[2] == UINT32_MAX && val[3] == UINT32_MAX;
4030 InstructionOperand dst = g.DefineAsRegister(node);
4031 if (all_zeros) {
4032 Emit(kArmS128Zero, dst);
4033 } else if (all_ones) {
4034 Emit(kArmS128AllOnes, dst);
4035 } else {
4036 Emit(kArmS128Const, dst, g.UseImmediate(val[0]), g.UseImmediate(val[1]),
4037 g.UseImmediate(val[2]), g.UseImmediate(val[3]));
4038 }
4039}

4043 ArmOperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(this);
4044 Emit(kArmS128Zero, g.DefineAsRegister(node));
4045}

4211#define VISIT_SIMD_ADD(Type, PairwiseType, NeonWidth) \
4212 template <> \
4213 void InstructionSelectorT<TurboshaftAdapter>::Visit##Type##Add( \
4214 node_t node) { \
4215 using namespace turboshaft; /*NOLINT(build/namespaces)*/ \
4216 ArmOperandGeneratorT<TurboshaftAdapter> g(this); \
4217 const Simd128BinopOp& add_op = Get(node).Cast<Simd128BinopOp>(); \
4218 const Operation& left = Get(add_op.left()); \
4219 const Operation& right = Get(add_op.right()); \
4220 if (left.Is<Opmask::kSimd128##Type##ExtAddPairwise##PairwiseType##S>() && \
4221 CanCover(node, add_op.left())) { \
4222 Emit(kArmVpadal | MiscField::encode(NeonS##NeonWidth), \
4223 g.DefineSameAsFirst(node), g.UseRegister(add_op.right()), \
4224 g.UseRegister(left.input(0))); \
4225 return; \
4226 } \
4227 if (left.Is<Opmask::kSimd128##Type##ExtAddPairwise##PairwiseType##U>() && \
4228 CanCover(node, add_op.left())) { \
4229 Emit(kArmVpadal | MiscField::encode(NeonU##NeonWidth), \
4230 g.DefineSameAsFirst(node), g.UseRegister(add_op.right()), \
4231 g.UseRegister(left.input(0))); \
4232 return; \
4233 } \
4234 if (right.Is<Opmask::kSimd128##Type##ExtAddPairwise##PairwiseType##S>() && \
4235 CanCover(node, add_op.right())) { \
4236 Emit(kArmVpadal | MiscField::encode(NeonS##NeonWidth), \
4237 g.DefineSameAsFirst(node), g.UseRegister(add_op.left()), \
4238 g.UseRegister(right.input(0))); \
4239 return; \
4240 } \
4241 if (right.Is<Opmask::kSimd128##Type##ExtAddPairwise##PairwiseType##U>() && \
4242 CanCover(node, add_op.right())) { \
4243 Emit(kArmVpadal | MiscField::encode(NeonU##NeonWidth), \
4244 g.DefineSameAsFirst(node), g.UseRegister(add_op.left()), \
4245 g.UseRegister(right.input(0))); \
4246 return; \
4247 } \
4248 VisitRRR(this, kArm##Type##Add, node); \

4464bool TryMatchArchShuffle(const uint8_t* shuffle, const ShuffleEntry* table,
4465 size_t num_entries, bool is_swizzle,
4466 ArchOpcode* opcode) {
4467 uint8_t mask = is_swizzle ? kSimd128Size - 1 : 2 * kSimd128Size - 1;
4468 for (size_t i = 0; i < num_entries; ++i) {
4469 const ShuffleEntry& entry = table[i];
4470 int j = 0;
4471 for (; j < kSimd128Size; ++j) {
4472 if ((entry.shuffle[j] & mask) != (shuffle[j] & mask)) {
4473 break;
4474 }
4475 }
4476 if (j == kSimd128Size) {
4477 *opcode = entry.opcode;
4478 return true;
4479 }
4480 }
4481 return false;
4482}
4483
4484template <typename Adapter>
4485void ArrangeShuffleTable(ArmOperandGeneratorT<Adapter>* g,
4486 typename Adapter::node_t input0,
4487 typename Adapter::node_t input1,
4488 InstructionOperand* src0, InstructionOperand* src1) {
4489 if (input0 == input1) {
4490 // Unary, any q-register can be the table.
4491 *src0 = *src1 = g->UseRegister(input0);
4492 } else {
4493 // Binary, table registers must be consecutive.
4494 *src0 = g->UseFixed(input0, q0);
4495 *src1 = g->UseFixed(input1, q1);
4496 }
4497}

4501template <typename Adapter>
4502void InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>::VisitI8x16Shuffle(node_t node) {
4503 uint8_t shuffle[kSimd128Size];
4504 bool is_swizzle;
4505 // TODO(nicohartmann@): Properly use view here once Turboshaft support is
4506 // implemented.
4507 auto view = this->simd_shuffle_view(node);
4508 CanonicalizeShuffle(view, shuffle, &is_swizzle);
4509 node_t input0 = view.input(0);
4510 node_t input1 = view.input(1);
4511 uint8_t shuffle32x4[4];
4512 ArmOperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(this);
4513 int index = 0;
4514 if (wasm::SimdShuffle::TryMatch32x4Shuffle(shuffle, shuffle32x4)) {
4515 if (wasm::SimdShuffle::TryMatchSplat<4>(shuffle, &index)) {
4516 DCHECK_GT(4, index);
4517 Emit(kArmS128Dup, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(input0),
4518 g.UseImmediate(Neon32), g.UseImmediate(index % 4));
4519 } else if (wasm::SimdShuffle::TryMatchIdentity(shuffle)) {
4520 // Bypass normal shuffle code generation in this case.
4521 // EmitIdentity
4522 MarkAsUsed(input0);
4523 MarkAsDefined(node);
4524 SetRename(node, input0);
4525 } else {
4526 // 32x4 shuffles are implemented as s-register moves. To simplify these,
4527 // make sure the destination is distinct from both sources.
4528 InstructionOperand src0 = g.UseUniqueRegister(input0);
4529 InstructionOperand src1 = is_swizzle ? src0 : g.UseUniqueRegister(input1);
4530 Emit(kArmS32x4Shuffle, g.DefineAsRegister(node), src0, src1,
4531 g.UseImmediate(wasm::SimdShuffle::Pack4Lanes(shuffle32x4)));
4532 }
4533 return;
4534 }
4535 if (wasm::SimdShuffle::TryMatchSplat<8>(shuffle, &index)) {
4536 DCHECK_GT(8, index);
4537 Emit(kArmS128Dup, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(input0),
4538 g.UseImmediate(Neon16), g.UseImmediate(index % 8));
4539 return;
4540 }
4541 if (wasm::SimdShuffle::TryMatchSplat<16>(shuffle, &index)) {
4542 DCHECK_GT(16, index);
4543 Emit(kArmS128Dup, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(input0),
4544 g.UseImmediate(Neon8), g.UseImmediate(index % 16));
4545 return;
4546 }
4547 ArchOpcode opcode;
4548 if (TryMatchArchShuffle(shuffle, arch_shuffles, arraysize(arch_shuffles),
4549 is_swizzle, &opcode)) {
4550 VisitRRRShuffle(this, opcode, node, input0, input1);
4551 return;
4552 }
4553 uint8_t offset;
4554 if (wasm::SimdShuffle::TryMatchConcat(shuffle, &offset)) {
4555 Emit(kArmS8x16Concat, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(input0),
4556 g.UseRegister(input1), g.UseImmediate(offset));
4557 return;
4558 }
4559 // Code generator uses vtbl, arrange sources to form a valid lookup table.
4560 InstructionOperand src0, src1;
4561 ArrangeShuffleTable(&g, input0, input1, &src0, &src1);
4562 Emit(kArmI8x16Shuffle, g.DefineAsRegister(node), src0, src1,
4563 g.UseImmediate(wasm::SimdShuffle::Pack4Lanes(shuffle)),
4564 g.UseImmediate(wasm::SimdShuffle::Pack4Lanes(shuffle + 4)),
4565 g.UseImmediate(wasm::SimdShuffle::Pack4Lanes(shuffle + 8)),
4566 g.UseImmediate(wasm::SimdShuffle::Pack4Lanes(shuffle + 12)));
4567}

4799template <typename Adapter>
4800void InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>::VisitTruncateFloat32ToInt32(node_t node) {
4801 ArmOperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(this);
4802 if constexpr (Adapter::IsTurboshaft) {
4803 using namespace turboshaft; // NOLINT(build/namespaces)
4804 const Operation& op = this->Get(node);
4805 InstructionCode opcode = kArmVcvtS32F32;
4806 if (op.Is<Opmask::kTruncateFloat32ToInt32OverflowToMin>()) {
4807 opcode |= MiscField::encode(true);
4808 }
4809 Emit(opcode, g.DefineAsRegister(node),
4810 g.UseRegister(this->input_at(node, 0)));
4811 } else {
4812 InstructionCode opcode = kArmVcvtS32F32;
4813 TruncateKind kind = OpParameter<TruncateKind>(node->op());
4814 if (kind == TruncateKind::kSetOverflowToMin) {
4815 opcode |= MiscField::encode(true);
4816 }
4817
4818 Emit(opcode, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(node->InputAt(0)));
4819 }
4820}

4822template <typename Adapter>
4823void InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>::VisitTruncateFloat32ToUint32(node_t node) {
4824 ArmOperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(this);
4825 if constexpr (Adapter::IsTurboshaft) {
4826 using namespace turboshaft; // NOLINT(build/namespaces)
4827 const Operation& op = this->Get(node);
4828 InstructionCode opcode = kArmVcvtU32F32;
4829 if (op.Is<Opmask::kTruncateFloat32ToUint32OverflowToMin>()) {
4830 opcode |= MiscField::encode(true);
4831 }
4832
4833 Emit(opcode, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(op.input(0)));
4834 } else {
4835 InstructionCode opcode = kArmVcvtU32F32;
4836 TruncateKind kind = OpParameter<TruncateKind>(node->op());
4837 if (kind == TruncateKind::kSetOverflowToMin) {
4838 opcode |= MiscField::encode(true);
4839 }
4840
4841 Emit(opcode, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(node->InputAt(0)));
4842 }
4843}

4851// static
4852MachineOperatorBuilder::Flags
4853InstructionSelector::SupportedMachineOperatorFlags() {
4854 MachineOperatorBuilder::Flags flags = MachineOperatorBuilder::kNoFlags;
4855 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(SUDIV)) {
4856 // The sdiv and udiv instructions correctly return 0 if the divisor is 0,
4857 // but the fall-back implementation does not.
4858 flags |= MachineOperatorBuilder::kInt32DivIsSafe |
4859 MachineOperatorBuilder::kUint32DivIsSafe;
4860 }
4861 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(ARMv7)) {
4862 flags |= MachineOperatorBuilder::kWord32ReverseBits;
4863 }
4864 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(ARMv8)) {
4865 flags |= MachineOperatorBuilder::kFloat32RoundDown |
4866 MachineOperatorBuilder::kFloat64RoundDown |
4867 MachineOperatorBuilder::kFloat32RoundUp |
4868 MachineOperatorBuilder::kFloat64RoundUp |
4869 MachineOperatorBuilder::kFloat32RoundTruncate |
4870 MachineOperatorBuilder::kFloat64RoundTruncate |
4871 MachineOperatorBuilder::kFloat64RoundTiesAway |
4872 MachineOperatorBuilder::kFloat32RoundTiesEven |
4873 MachineOperatorBuilder::kFloat64RoundTiesEven;
4874 }
4875 flags |= MachineOperatorBuilder::kSatConversionIsSafe;
4876 return flags;
4877}

4880MachineOperatorBuilder::AlignmentRequirements
4881InstructionSelector::AlignmentRequirements() {
4882 base::EnumSet<MachineRepresentation> req_aligned;
4883 req_aligned.Add(MachineRepresentation::kFloat32);
4884 req_aligned.Add(MachineRepresentation::kFloat64);
4885 return MachineOperatorBuilder::AlignmentRequirements::
4886 SomeUnalignedAccessUnsupported(req_aligned, req_aligned);
4887}
